1
00:00:25,951 --> 00:00:28,954
SIX SINGLES UNDER ONE ROOF

2
00:00:29,822 --> 00:00:30,823
THE GUYS ARE BACK FROM THEIR OUTING

3
00:00:30,890 --> 00:00:33,893
<i>- I had a blast.</i>
<i>- Why am I the most tired?</i>

4
00:00:33,959 --> 00:00:35,828
<i>Good work.</i>

5
00:00:39,098 --> 00:00:41,634
- We've got a big pile again.
- What?

6
00:00:41,967 --> 00:00:44,870
DELIVERIES OF KEUN-SUK'S ORDERS

7
00:00:45,137 --> 00:00:46,138
What's all that?

8
00:00:46,205 --> 00:00:48,374
- Just some stuff I ordered.
- Why are there so many boxes?

9
00:00:48,440 --> 00:00:50,142
Why did you order so much stuff?

10
00:00:50,209 --> 00:00:51,343
It's a surprise.

11
00:00:51,410 --> 00:00:52,611
HOUSEMATES ARE ASTOUNDED
BY ALL THE PACKAGES

12
00:00:53,012 --> 00:00:54,013
GROANS

13
00:00:54,079 --> 00:00:55,447
CHANTS

14
00:00:55,514 --> 00:00:57,316
Why did you order so much stuff?

15
00:00:57,683 --> 00:00:58,717
BIG SPENDER IS UP TO SOMETHING

16
00:00:58,784 --> 00:01:00,853
Help me move these inside, please.

17
00:01:01,186 --> 00:01:02,388
GROANS

18
00:01:02,454 --> 00:01:03,756
GASPS

19
00:01:03,822 --> 00:01:05,658
SOO-JIN HAS BEEN ENJOYING
SOME QUALITY ALONE TIME

20
00:01:05,724 --> 00:01:06,825
Hey, you guys.

21
00:01:09,228 --> 00:01:10,462
What on earth is this?

22
00:01:11,597 --> 00:01:12,665
What is it?

23
00:01:12,932 --> 00:01:14,934
I guess Santa Claus paid us a visit.

24
00:01:15,568 --> 00:01:17,603
PRESENTS?

25
00:01:18,037 --> 00:01:19,171
A SERIES OF BOXES

26
00:01:19,238 --> 00:01:20,973
ARE ALL OF THESE
FROM SANTA CLAUS JANG?

27
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:22,041
GASPS

28
00:01:22,675 --> 00:01:27,212
WHAT DID KEUN-SUK GET
FOR HIS STILL IMMATURE FRIENDS?

29
00:01:27,546 --> 00:01:28,547
GASPS

30
00:01:29,848 --> 00:01:31,250
What's all this?

31
00:01:31,584 --> 00:01:32,685
I have no idea.

32
00:01:33,519 --> 00:01:34,520
HE ONLY DID AS HE WAS TOLD

33
00:01:34,587 --> 00:01:36,689
I guess Keun-suk prepared a surprise.

34
00:01:38,257 --> 00:01:40,259
Gosh, you bought so much stuff.

35
00:01:40,326 --> 00:01:41,794
WHAT EXACTLY IS HE PLANNING TO DO?

36
00:01:41,860 --> 00:01:43,929
What's with all these boxes?

37
00:01:43,996 --> 00:01:45,230
That's what I'm wondering.

38
00:01:45,297 --> 00:01:46,632
Are they for interior decoration?

39
00:01:46,966 --> 00:01:48,067
Hey, what's all this?

40
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:49,935
Look forward to it.

41
00:01:50,002 --> 00:01:51,837
I made the big decision

42
00:01:52,338 --> 00:01:53,505
to splurge a little.

43
00:01:54,273 --> 00:01:59,945
FROM OCTOPUS TO HELICOPTER RIDES
WHAT IS HE UP TO?

44
00:02:00,012 --> 00:02:02,414
What's with all these boxes?

45
00:02:02,481 --> 00:02:03,716
I'll take care of everything.

46
00:02:03,782 --> 00:02:04,883
Give me a second.

47
00:02:05,317 --> 00:02:08,821
AS THE GUYS GET CHANGED

48
00:02:10,623 --> 00:02:15,394
SOO-JIN BRINGS IN ANOTHER BOX

49
00:02:16,195 --> 00:02:19,932
HAS SOO-JIN ORDERED SOMETHING, TOO?

50
00:02:20,466 --> 00:02:24,403
HEADS STRAIGHT TO THE SINK
WITH THE MYSTERY POUCH

51
00:02:25,037 --> 00:02:29,842
IS SOO-JIN PREPARING
A SURPRISE EVENT, TOO?

52
00:02:30,376 --> 00:02:32,311
- What's up?
- What?

53
00:02:32,378 --> 00:02:33,579
- What are you doing?
- Me?

54
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:36,882
- These taste amazing raw.
- Yes.

55
00:02:36,949 --> 00:02:40,052
I thought I'd dress some
so we can enjoy them together.

56
00:02:41,020 --> 00:02:42,087
What have you got there?

57
00:02:42,154 --> 00:02:44,289
- You mentioned these in chat, right?
- Yes.

58
00:02:44,356 --> 00:02:45,357
- Yes, stalked sea squirts.
- What was it?

59
00:02:45,424 --> 00:02:46,492
- Stalked sea squirts?
- I got some.

60
00:02:47,092 --> 00:02:48,093
I ordered them.

61
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:50,362
- Did they come in?
- Yes, they did.

62
00:02:50,429 --> 00:02:51,597
RAW STALKED SEA SQUIRTS?

63
00:02:52,197 --> 00:02:54,533
- I ordered them.
- Are you dressing them now?

64
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:55,701
Yes, I'm going over them

65
00:02:55,768 --> 00:02:58,671
to find ones we can eat raw.

66
00:02:58,737 --> 00:03:01,240
They look good. How do you eat them?
Do you dip it in <i>chogochujang?</i>

67
00:03:01,573 --> 00:03:03,742
- You need to cut it in half
- Yes.

68
00:03:03,809 --> 00:03:04,943
to remove sand.

69
00:03:05,010 --> 00:03:06,111
Then, you eat it as is.

70
00:03:07,046 --> 00:03:08,847
FASCINATING

71
00:03:09,081 --> 00:03:10,082
They look like sausages.

72
00:03:10,149 --> 00:03:11,250
UPSIDE OF LIVING TOGETHER
TRYING NEW FOODS

73
00:03:11,316 --> 00:03:13,318
- You think so?
- Tiny ones.

74
00:03:13,819 --> 00:03:16,188
First off, I need to dress them.

75
00:03:16,255 --> 00:03:17,723
Do you want me to open them?

76
00:03:18,290 --> 00:03:19,825
All right. Hear me out.

77
00:03:20,292 --> 00:03:22,695
- I'll fill you in on my plan.
- Okay.

78
00:03:22,761 --> 00:03:26,799
I want us to visit Japan again.

79
00:03:27,433 --> 00:03:28,667
Again?

80
00:03:29,101 --> 00:03:30,502
I'd love that.

81
00:03:30,569 --> 00:03:32,871
When we go to Japan again...

82
00:03:33,072 --> 00:03:34,406
We can visit Osaka this time.

83
00:03:36,208 --> 00:03:37,209
No.

84
00:03:37,276 --> 00:03:38,277
WAIT FOR IT

85
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:39,845
I'm turning this place
into a sushi bar.

86
00:03:39,912 --> 00:03:41,180
Goodness.

87
00:03:41,246 --> 00:03:42,514
Seriously?

88
00:03:42,581 --> 00:03:44,149
YOU'RE TURNING OUR HOME
INTO A SUSHI BAR?

89
00:03:44,983 --> 00:03:46,652
I'll be your sushi chef for the day.

90
00:03:47,186 --> 00:03:48,987
What have we got here, then?

91
00:03:49,054 --> 00:03:51,423
WHAT IS IN THESE BOXES?

92
00:03:51,490 --> 00:03:53,092
A setup for conveyor belt sushi.

93
00:03:53,625 --> 00:03:54,793
Is it conveyor belt sushi?

94
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:57,262
- Is it a conveyor chain?
- Of course.

95
00:03:57,329 --> 00:03:59,231
DID HE ACTUALLY ORDER
A CONVEYOR CHAIN?

96
00:03:59,698 --> 00:04:01,166
A CONVEYOR CHAIN ON OUR DINING TABLE?

97
00:04:01,233 --> 00:04:02,835
- Is it really a conveyor chain?
- That's hilarious.

98
00:04:02,901 --> 00:04:04,002
- Is it conveyor belt sushi?
- We'll get right on it.

99
00:04:04,069 --> 00:04:05,537
AP KNOWS NO LIMITS

100
00:04:06,238 --> 00:04:09,074
In that case, can I go make a soup?

101
00:04:09,141 --> 00:04:10,709
- Of course.
- How about some soybean paste soup?

102
00:04:10,776 --> 00:04:12,111
- You're making soup?
- Well...

103
00:04:12,177 --> 00:04:14,313
- Soup with stalked sea squirts.
- Sounds lovely.

104
00:04:14,513 --> 00:04:16,148
- Right?
- I'd love some hot soup.

105
00:04:16,215 --> 00:04:17,216
THEY ARE ALL IN TUNE NOW

106
00:04:17,850 --> 00:04:19,418
LET'S OPEN THE FIRST BOX!

107
00:04:19,485 --> 00:04:20,719
Obviously...

108
00:04:21,253 --> 00:04:22,488
CURIOUS

109
00:04:22,821 --> 00:04:24,256
I had to bring in a lucky cat.

110
00:04:24,490 --> 00:04:25,691
I had to bring in a lucky cat.

111
00:04:28,293 --> 00:04:29,795
- These are everywhere in Japan.
- You bet.

112
00:04:29,862 --> 00:04:31,096
It should wave its arm, too.

113
00:04:31,163 --> 00:04:32,598
I'll make it happen right away.

114
00:04:33,098 --> 00:04:34,600
<i>It's waving now, all right.</i>

115
00:04:34,666 --> 00:04:36,168
IT'S TIME TO PREPARE DINNER

116
00:04:36,235 --> 00:04:38,771
When we do it, we do it right.

117
00:04:39,071 --> 00:04:40,205
Seriously.

118
00:04:40,272 --> 00:04:41,306
PASSIONATE PARTY PLANNER JANG

119
00:04:41,373 --> 00:04:43,942
<i>I worked on the list all night</i>

120
00:04:44,009 --> 00:04:45,878
<i>and placed an order</i>
<i>with a quick delivery option.</i>

121
00:04:45,944 --> 00:04:47,146
<i>You really are something else.</i>

122
00:04:47,412 --> 00:04:48,580
This should be fun.

123
00:04:49,148 --> 00:04:50,983
- Up next...
- This will get our appetites going.

124
00:04:51,049 --> 00:04:52,151
Look at this rice basket.

125
00:04:52,718 --> 00:04:55,120
Don't let this surprise you.
This is only the tip of the iceberg.

126
00:04:55,187 --> 00:04:57,256
DETAIL-ORIENTED KEUN-SUK
BOUGHT THE RICE BASKET

127
00:04:57,489 --> 00:04:59,491
- You're something else.
- Guys.

128
00:04:59,558 --> 00:05:00,893
Your attention, please.

129
00:05:01,093 --> 00:05:02,094
What is it?

130
00:05:03,028 --> 00:05:04,029
Ta-da.

131
00:05:04,797 --> 00:05:06,365
SHEER JOY

132
00:05:06,832 --> 00:05:08,267
ARE YOU THAT DELIGHTED?

133
00:05:09,067 --> 00:05:12,905
LIFE IS NEVER BORING
WHEN YOU LIVE WITH AP

134
00:05:12,971 --> 00:05:14,706
I've got everything, right?

135
00:05:14,773 --> 00:05:16,308
- Look, Da-hee.
- Ta-da.

136
00:05:16,642 --> 00:05:17,776
What's all this?

137
00:05:18,610 --> 00:05:19,645
Ta-da.

138
00:05:20,045 --> 00:05:21,980
SPOOKED

139
00:05:22,047 --> 00:05:24,316
Keun-suk's offering
sushi omakase this evening.

140
00:05:24,383 --> 00:05:25,384
- Sushi omakase?
- Da-hee.

141
00:05:25,450 --> 00:05:26,652
You guys didn't get to join us

142
00:05:26,718 --> 00:05:28,787
- and Soo-jin didn't get her sushi.
- The lucky cat.

143
00:05:28,854 --> 00:05:31,390
I'm setting up a sushi bar at home.

144
00:05:32,157 --> 00:05:33,492
- For the fun of it.
- Look at Da-hee.

145
00:05:34,259 --> 00:05:36,995
FORGET SUSHI

146
00:05:37,696 --> 00:05:38,964
- For the fun of it.
- Look at Da-hee.

147
00:05:39,031 --> 00:05:41,433
DA-HEE IS TRAUMATIZED
BY THE MESS ON THE TABLE

148
00:05:42,668 --> 00:05:43,902
This is so funny.

149
00:05:44,570 --> 00:05:46,572
What do you think?
I know it's a mess here. Hang on.

150
00:05:46,638 --> 00:05:47,639
GUYS START TIDYING UP

151
00:05:47,706 --> 00:05:49,208
Wait, after this...

152
00:05:49,274 --> 00:05:51,543
- Why do we need a glue gun?
- I'll need it later

153
00:05:51,610 --> 00:05:55,047
to glue the plates
to the conveyor chain system.

154
00:05:55,848 --> 00:05:57,983
Da-hee, he prepared
a conveyor chain system.

155
00:05:58,951 --> 00:05:59,952
A WINNING SMILE

156
00:06:00,018 --> 00:06:02,120
- A real conveyor chain system.
- Really?

157
00:06:02,187 --> 00:06:04,223
- Really?
- Here's the supply for the chain.

158
00:06:04,623 --> 00:06:06,358
- An actual moving chain?
- Sure.

159
00:06:06,892 --> 00:06:07,926
I'm building it here.

160
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:11,964
How do you think of these ideas?

161
00:06:12,030 --> 00:06:13,198
AP WILL MAKE YOU SPEECHLESS

162
00:06:13,265 --> 00:06:14,433
He's on another level, right?

163
00:06:14,499 --> 00:06:15,500
I can't even...

164
00:06:15,567 --> 00:06:16,768
He took me by surprise, too.

165
00:06:17,135 --> 00:06:19,304
I'm just mind-blown.

166
00:06:19,771 --> 00:06:22,541
- I'll treat you to a real meal.
- What is this?

167
00:06:22,975 --> 00:06:24,076
WHERE IS THE CONVEYOR SYSTEM?

168
00:06:24,142 --> 00:06:25,444
Hey.

169
00:06:25,978 --> 00:06:28,046
JAE-HYEON IS STARTLED
BY THE CONTENT IN THE BOX

170
00:06:28,113 --> 00:06:30,215
Be real with me. Isn't it impressive?

171
00:06:30,716 --> 00:06:31,884
What's this?

172
00:06:32,684 --> 00:06:35,387
This will be my conveyor system.

173
00:06:35,454 --> 00:06:36,455
KEY OF CONVEYOR BELT SUSHI

174
00:06:36,521 --> 00:06:38,457
IS A TOY TRAIN?

175
00:06:38,523 --> 00:06:40,125
This will be my conveyor system.

176
00:06:40,192 --> 00:06:41,193
Hey!

177
00:06:42,961 --> 00:06:44,897
Why, you little...

178
00:06:44,963 --> 00:06:48,533
Considering the helicopter ride

179
00:06:48,867 --> 00:06:51,870
I thought he might actually set up
a real conveyor system.

180
00:06:51,937 --> 00:06:53,605
In reality, he brought this toy.

181
00:06:53,672 --> 00:06:55,807
IT'S A MINIATURE TRAIN
FOR LITTLE ANIMAL TOYS

182
00:06:55,874 --> 00:06:57,242
It really works, okay?

183
00:06:57,309 --> 00:06:58,343
Have some faith in me.

184
00:06:58,944 --> 00:06:59,945
What's going on?

185
00:07:00,012 --> 00:07:01,113
CAPTAIN KYUNG ARRIVES BELATEDLY

186
00:07:01,179 --> 00:07:02,180
What's this?

187
00:07:04,316 --> 00:07:05,918
- But...
- I want the black one.

188
00:07:05,984 --> 00:07:07,052
How on earth...

189
00:07:07,119 --> 00:07:09,321
How will you move sushi with this?

190
00:07:09,388 --> 00:07:10,389
With the full track?

191
00:07:10,455 --> 00:07:11,857
I've done it before. It works.

192
00:07:12,524 --> 00:07:13,558
You've done it before?

193
00:07:14,026 --> 00:07:15,394
Multiple times at that.

194
00:07:15,727 --> 00:07:17,396
I'm a master with this thing.

195
00:07:17,996 --> 00:07:23,368
VETERAN OF SUSHI CONVEYOR SYSTEM
MADE UP OF TOY TRAIN

196
00:07:23,835 --> 00:07:26,705
You're really living your best life.

197
00:07:27,072 --> 00:07:29,141
- That's insane.
- It works, for sure.

198
00:07:29,574 --> 00:07:30,575
Where is Daniel?

199
00:07:31,243 --> 00:07:32,811
He's back. He's upstairs.

200
00:07:33,178 --> 00:07:36,081
BUT ON THE 2ND FLOOR

201
00:07:36,148 --> 00:07:38,583
DANIEL IS NOWHERE TO BE FOUND

202
00:07:40,352 --> 00:07:44,456
HE IS NOT IN THE HOUSE
NOR OUT IN THE YARD

203
00:07:45,057 --> 00:07:47,359
WHERE IS DANIEL?

204
00:07:47,426 --> 00:07:49,328
<i>- Hello.</i>
<i>- Hello.</i>

205
00:07:53,065 --> 00:07:54,099
HE SNUCK OUT TO A CAFÉ NEARBY

206
00:07:54,166 --> 00:07:55,267
Goodness.

207
00:07:57,102 --> 00:08:00,939
WHY IS HE OUT HERE ALONE THIS LATE?

208
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:06,078
HE LOOKS NERVOUS
AS IF HE IS WAITING FOR SOMEONE

209
00:08:09,314 --> 00:08:13,719
WHO IS HE EXPECTING TO SEE?

210
00:08:14,319 --> 00:08:20,058
SOMEONE APPROACHES THE CAFÉ
WITH LONG STRIDES AT THE MOMENT

211
00:08:20,125 --> 00:08:21,226
SUCKS IN BREATH

212
00:08:21,293 --> 00:08:24,463
I think she's a latte person.

213
00:08:25,931 --> 00:08:30,102
WHO IS THE MYSTERY WOMAN
WHO LIKES LATTE?

214
00:08:31,136 --> 00:08:32,971
SMILES

215
00:08:33,038 --> 00:08:34,906
- It's freezing.
- It's cold, right?

216
00:08:34,973 --> 00:08:36,141
- Hey.
- Did you go out like that?

217
00:08:36,675 --> 00:08:37,976
- Seriously?
- I'm so cold.

218
00:08:38,043 --> 00:08:40,212
- Isn't it unbearably cold?
- You bet it is.

219
00:08:40,746 --> 00:08:42,414
You could catch a cold.

220
00:08:42,481 --> 00:08:44,149
- I didn't know it'd be so cold.
- Goodness.

221
00:08:44,883 --> 00:08:48,720
JUST EARLIER IN DANIEL'S ROOM

222
00:08:49,154 --> 00:08:50,756
WHEN ARE YOU COMING HOME, DO-YEON?

223
00:08:50,822 --> 00:08:52,157
LET ME KNOW BEFORE YOU ARRIVE

224
00:08:52,224 --> 00:08:53,725
LET'S GRAB A COFFEE AT A NEARBY CAFÉ

225
00:08:53,792 --> 00:08:55,460
MY SHOOT WRAPPED UP JUST NOW

226
00:08:55,527 --> 00:08:58,030
I'LL TELL YOU WHEN I'M ALMOST THERE

227
00:08:58,096 --> 00:08:59,097
OKAY!

228
00:08:59,731 --> 00:09:05,070
FOR SOME REASON,
HE SET UP A COFFEE DATE WITH DO-YEON

229
00:09:05,804 --> 00:09:08,774
WHILE HIS HOUSEMATES
WERE BUSY PREPARING DINNER

230
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:14,046
HE SNUCK OUT QUIETLY

231
00:09:14,513 --> 00:09:15,781
Did you come from home?

232
00:09:15,847 --> 00:09:17,749
Yes, but we just got back.

233
00:09:17,816 --> 00:09:18,884
Just about 30 minutes or so.

234
00:09:19,718 --> 00:09:21,219
- Did you come here right away?
- Yeah.

235
00:09:21,286 --> 00:09:22,721
What were you doing alone?

236
00:09:23,855 --> 00:09:25,023
I just sat around

237
00:09:26,158 --> 00:09:27,325
to get a coffee with you.

238
00:09:28,927 --> 00:09:30,695
JUST THE TWO OF US?

239
00:09:30,862 --> 00:09:32,697
I don't want coffee. I'm too sleepy.

240
00:09:33,465 --> 00:09:34,499
I know, right?

241
00:09:34,566 --> 00:09:35,901
I'm getting milk tea myself.

242
00:09:39,337 --> 00:09:40,338
Well...

243
00:09:41,540 --> 00:09:44,342
It's fun to be with everyone.

244
00:09:44,409 --> 00:09:45,811
But when we're by ourselves

245
00:09:45,877 --> 00:09:47,379
we can have a private chat.

246
00:09:47,879 --> 00:09:48,880
So...

247
00:09:50,582 --> 00:09:51,583
Okay, then.

248
00:09:51,650 --> 00:09:52,984
Don't tell me you need a loan.

249
00:09:53,051 --> 00:09:54,152
Of course not.

250
00:09:54,219 --> 00:09:56,054
- You can talk to Keun-suk for that.
- Sure.

251
00:09:56,121 --> 00:09:57,622
- Thank goodness.
- Not at all.

252
00:09:57,689 --> 00:09:59,958
- I'm so relieved.
- It's just...

253
00:10:00,892 --> 00:10:02,227
I originally thought...

254
00:10:02,294 --> 00:10:03,295
CAUTIOUSLY OPENS UP

255
00:10:03,495 --> 00:10:05,697
...I'd have a hard time
getting along with you.

