00:19:09,140 --> 00:19:11,142
I guess he made a grand preparation.

504
00:19:11,209 --> 00:19:13,144
He might come downstairs
wearing a tall chef's hat.

505
00:19:13,211 --> 00:19:15,046
- He might actually do that.
- Come on.

506
00:19:15,113 --> 00:19:16,147
Don't be silly.

507
00:19:17,782 --> 00:19:21,586
MEANWHILE, UPSTAIRS,
KEUN-SUK GRABS HIS PORTABLE SPEAKER

508
00:19:21,653 --> 00:19:23,855
AND STARTS PLAYING
AN ENTRANCE SONG FOR HIMSELF

509
00:19:24,322 --> 00:19:26,624
- These cats bring good luck.
- I hear music. How ominous.

510
00:19:26,691 --> 00:19:27,692
What's going on?

511
00:19:28,526 --> 00:19:30,628
Guys, I'm worried.
That must be Keun-suk playing it.

512
00:19:30,695 --> 00:19:33,197
AP NEVER MAKES A BORING ENTRANCE

513
00:19:33,731 --> 00:19:35,133
SOFT STEPS

514
00:19:35,199 --> 00:19:36,200
- What?
- What?

515
00:19:36,267 --> 00:19:37,335
Something's off.

516
00:19:37,702 --> 00:19:39,137
I knew it!

517
00:19:39,203 --> 00:19:40,538
- There he is.
- Just look at him.

518
00:19:41,105 --> 00:19:42,440
I knew it!

519
00:19:42,507 --> 00:19:44,208
MASTER SUSHI CHEF AT YOUR SERVICE

520
00:19:45,410 --> 00:19:48,413
ALWAYS GOING THE EXTRA MILE

521
00:19:48,846 --> 00:19:50,281
HE'S DONE IT AGAIN

522
00:19:50,882 --> 00:19:52,050
YET ANOTHER RUCKUS STARTS

523
00:19:52,116 --> 00:19:53,785
Keun-chan.

524
00:19:53,851 --> 00:19:56,621
You are heartily welcome
to Jang Keun-suk's sushi restaurant.

525
00:19:56,688 --> 00:19:57,955
Thank you for your patronage.

526
00:19:58,589 --> 00:20:02,760
WE APPLAUD YOU FOR YOUR ENTHUSIASM

527
00:20:02,827 --> 00:20:05,363
Please enjoy this evening.
I'd appreciate it very much.

528
00:20:05,430 --> 00:20:06,764
AP'S DINNER SERVICE

529
00:20:06,998 --> 00:20:08,499
I'll go bring the sushi.

530
00:20:09,767 --> 00:20:10,902
Was that necessary, though?

531
00:20:11,469 --> 00:20:12,637
He's acting up today.

532
00:20:13,571 --> 00:20:15,173
- But he's earned it.
- Let's go easy on him.

533
00:20:15,239 --> 00:20:17,141
- Okay, we'll cut him some slack.
- This is hilarious.

534
00:20:17,775 --> 00:20:20,645
HYGIENE COMES FIRST

535
00:20:21,312 --> 00:20:25,016
BRINGS OUT TODAY'S SASHIMI
WITH A PROFESSIONAL'S ENERGY

536
00:20:26,150 --> 00:20:27,852
Don't I deserve to act up a little?

537
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:32,457
Here are your sushi toppings.

538
00:20:32,523 --> 00:20:35,093
PREMIUM AGED SASHIMI
AP SELECTED FOR HIS HOUSEMATES

539
00:20:35,593 --> 00:20:37,328
EXCITEMENT GOES THROUGH THE ROOF

540
00:20:37,962 --> 00:20:39,597
IT LOOKS DELICIOUS

541
00:20:40,198 --> 00:20:41,566
I hope I'm good enough.

542
00:20:41,632 --> 00:20:42,800
You're my customers for the day.

543
00:20:42,867 --> 00:20:45,069
- Can we chat by ourselves, then?
- Of course.

544
00:20:45,336 --> 00:20:47,105
- I'll prepare sushi without talking.
- All right.

545
00:20:47,171 --> 00:20:49,006
Really? Okay.

546
00:20:49,073 --> 00:20:50,274
AP TRANSFORMS INTO A SUSHI CHEF

547
00:20:50,341 --> 00:20:51,342
BLOWS OUT AIR

548
00:20:51,676 --> 00:20:54,212
REMOVES ALL THE FINE DUST

549
00:20:54,278 --> 00:20:55,480
We've got a few pieces left here.

550
00:20:55,546 --> 00:20:56,581
DIPS HIS HANDS IN VINEGAR SAUCE

551
00:20:58,716 --> 00:21:00,885
- Keun-suk is going all out.
- I know.

552
00:21:00,952 --> 00:21:02,153
CLEARLY TRIED THIS BEFORE

553
00:21:02,220 --> 00:21:03,721
That's so cool.

554
00:21:03,788 --> 00:21:04,889
He's got skills.

555
00:21:04,956 --> 00:21:06,224
ALWAYS EARNEST WITH FOOD

556
00:21:06,891 --> 00:21:09,761
WE CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE ACTUALLY DOING THIS AT HOME

557
00:21:09,827 --> 00:21:11,195
How fascinating.

558
00:21:11,262 --> 00:21:13,698
ADD THE TOPPING

559
00:21:14,232 --> 00:21:16,701
FIRST PIECE OF SUSHI
IS COMING ALONG NICELY

560
00:21:16,768 --> 00:21:17,769
Would you look at that?

561
00:21:17,835 --> 00:21:18,970
He's petting it.

562
00:21:23,174 --> 00:21:24,275
PARDON?

563
00:21:24,342 --> 00:21:26,377
"He's petting it"?

564
00:21:26,944 --> 00:21:28,546
"Shape" would be appropriate

565
00:21:28,613 --> 00:21:30,214
- but you had to go for "pet."
- "Pet"?

566
00:21:30,414 --> 00:21:33,551
- "He's petting that sashimi."
- He's shaping it beautifully.

567
00:21:33,818 --> 00:21:36,020
What do you think?
Looks pretty good, right?

568
00:21:36,087 --> 00:21:37,555
Just a second.

569
00:21:37,989 --> 00:21:39,056
You look the part.

570
00:21:39,891 --> 00:21:41,292
Great.

571
00:21:41,492 --> 00:21:44,162
The train will depart
after five pieces are ready.

572
00:21:44,495 --> 00:21:46,397
The other plates want a passenger.

573
00:21:46,798 --> 00:21:48,232
Da-hee will have to press the button.

574
00:21:48,299 --> 00:21:49,367
- This one?
- Yes.

575
00:21:49,433 --> 00:21:51,636
- When it's ready, or right now?
- No, not yet.

576
00:21:51,702 --> 00:21:52,804
After five pieces are ready.

577
00:21:52,870 --> 00:21:54,138
I could press this now.

578
00:21:55,239 --> 00:21:57,175
I'm having so much fun.
This is amazing.

579
00:21:57,708 --> 00:21:58,810
You're so funny.

580
00:21:58,876 --> 00:22:00,278
LOCKING IN AGAIN

581
00:22:00,344 --> 00:22:02,346
- Keun-suk...
- Go on.

582
00:22:02,713 --> 00:22:04,315
Go on. Let's do this.

583
00:22:06,017 --> 00:22:07,718
HOME-MADE MEALS ARE ELEVATED

584
00:22:07,785 --> 00:22:10,021
WHEN AP IS YOUR HOUSEMATE

585
00:22:11,189 --> 00:22:13,658
He looks like a real chef
when he's focusing on sushi.

586
00:22:14,725 --> 00:22:16,994
A HABITUAL PRINCELY SMILE
IS ON THE HOUSE

587
00:22:17,562 --> 00:22:18,896
That looks great.

588
00:22:20,865 --> 00:22:23,034
- Conveyor belt sushi at home?
- I know.

589
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:24,202
I'm over the moon.

590
00:22:24,268 --> 00:22:25,670
I love sushi.

591
00:22:27,004 --> 00:22:28,372
<i>He's got skills.</i>

592
00:22:28,439 --> 00:22:31,275
<i>The train will depart</i>
<i>after five pieces are ready.</i>

593
00:22:31,342 --> 00:22:33,110
<i>He has that master's vibe.</i>

594
00:22:33,177 --> 00:22:35,179
- I'd like to announce
- Yes?

595
00:22:35,246 --> 00:22:37,248
that the sushi pieces are ready.

596
00:22:37,315 --> 00:22:40,117
Please turn on the train over there.
Da-hee will do the honors next.

597
00:22:40,184 --> 00:22:42,286
- Let the sushi trains depart.
- Here they go.

598
00:22:42,587 --> 00:22:44,522
Off they go!

599
00:22:45,323 --> 00:22:46,858
THIS IS EXCITING!

600
00:22:46,924 --> 00:22:47,959
- Let's go!
- Off they go!

601
00:22:48,759 --> 00:22:50,127
- What on earth?
- Let's go!

602
00:22:50,194 --> 00:22:51,495
Pick them up.

603
00:22:51,562 --> 00:22:52,797
Come on!

604
00:22:53,030 --> 00:22:55,166
- All right. Pick them up.
- Pick them up.

605
00:22:55,233 --> 00:22:56,901
- Right now?
- Do it.

606
00:22:57,368 --> 00:22:59,570
GET YOUR INNER CHILD READY
FOR THE SUSHI TRAINS

607
00:22:59,637 --> 00:23:00,738
What's this?

608
00:23:03,374 --> 00:23:04,475
MASTER PARTY PLANNER

609
00:23:04,542 --> 00:23:05,643
- What on earth?
- Hey!

610
00:23:05,710 --> 00:23:06,744
- This is the best.
- Someone is excited.

611
00:23:06,811 --> 00:23:09,280
- Look at him. He's loving this.
- It's so much fun.

612
00:23:10,815 --> 00:23:12,283
The sashimi's got wicked sheen.

613
00:23:12,350 --> 00:23:13,651
This is so fascinating.

614
00:23:13,718 --> 00:23:15,186
THE HOUSEMATES
HAVE PICKED UP KEUN-SUK'S SUSHI

615
00:23:15,753 --> 00:23:17,822
- Let me try this.
- Thanks for the food.

616
00:23:20,224 --> 00:23:21,492
RIGHT ON CUE

617
00:23:21,559 --> 00:23:25,596
EVERYONE EXCLAIMS IN APPRECIATION

618
00:23:25,663 --> 00:23:26,664
SATISFIED

619
00:23:26,731 --> 00:23:27,732
How is it?

620
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:30,801
EXCLAIMS

621
00:23:32,270 --> 00:23:33,838
Are they okay?

622
00:23:34,372 --> 00:23:36,474
- Better than you expected, right?
- Hey, wait.

623
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:39,176
- It's downright amazing.
- It's so good.

624
00:23:39,243 --> 00:23:40,444
This is great.

625
00:23:40,511 --> 00:23:41,712
It's good.

626
00:23:41,779 --> 00:23:43,214
You seasoned the rice just right.

627
00:23:43,814 --> 00:23:46,450
Today's my proudest moment
since we started filming.

628
00:23:46,517 --> 00:23:48,119
- You should have some, too.
- Dig in.

629
00:23:48,185 --> 00:23:50,755
I'm really enjoying this.

630
00:23:50,821 --> 00:23:52,757
It's exhilarating to see my work

631
00:23:52,823 --> 00:23:55,259
receive great feedback
right on the spot.

632
00:23:55,326 --> 00:23:56,494
- It's incredible.
- Really?

633
00:23:56,694 --> 00:23:57,862
It's so good.

634
00:24:00,665 --> 00:24:02,867
TRIES SOO-JIN'S STALKED SEA SQUIRT
SOYBEAN PASTE SOUP

635
00:24:02,934 --> 00:24:04,902
- The broth is to die for.
- Agreed.

636
00:24:04,969 --> 00:24:07,405
It tastes like the seafood soup
you get as a hangover cure.

637
00:24:08,739 --> 00:24:09,740
SATISFIED SIGH

638
00:24:10,441 --> 00:24:12,209
- Daniel's enjoying it.
- It's warm, too.

639
00:24:12,977 --> 00:24:14,445
Warm soup is the best
for chilly weather.

640
00:24:14,779 --> 00:24:17,014
What do you think, Daniel?
Is it good?

641
00:24:18,449 --> 00:24:20,651
NO EXPLANATION NEEDED

642
00:24:20,718 --> 00:24:21,953
It's so good.

643
00:24:22,019 --> 00:24:23,387
Gosh, this is so...

644
00:24:23,721 --> 00:24:25,556
- I love it.
- Hey, one train is back.

645
00:24:25,623 --> 00:24:26,824
It's right here.

646
00:24:26,891 --> 00:24:28,726
- Chef, we need five more pieces.
- Chef.

647
00:24:28,793 --> 00:24:31,862
<i>Just a minute</i>

648
00:24:33,597 --> 00:24:35,666
This is the first sushi of my life.

649
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:38,202
- Is it good?
- The soup is incredible.

650
00:24:38,469 --> 00:24:40,538
- Hey, sushi.
- Just the right texture...

651
00:24:41,572 --> 00:24:42,573
Hey!

652
00:24:42,640 --> 00:24:43,674
Just the right texture...

653
00:24:43,741 --> 00:24:44,976
THE PEACE WASN'T MEANT TO LAST

654
00:24:45,042 --> 00:24:46,277
- No!
- Your legs.

655
00:24:46,344 --> 00:24:48,012
- It's going off track! Turn it off!
- No.

656
00:24:48,079 --> 00:24:49,780
- Get this out of the way first.
- Turn it off!

657
00:24:49,847 --> 00:24:51,349
- What happened?
- How are your legs?

658
00:24:51,415 --> 00:24:53,084
- Are you okay?
- I'm good.

659
00:24:53,150 --> 00:24:54,719
- I'm really fine.
- You sure?

660
00:24:54,785 --> 00:24:55,786
It's just...

661
00:24:55,853 --> 00:24:56,887
Wipe your legs first.

662
00:24:56,954 --> 00:24:58,522
- I'm okay.
- Hurry.

663
00:24:58,589 --> 00:25:00,091
- Turn that off.
- I'm done.

664
00:25:00,157 --> 00:25:01,625
Can you stop the train for a bit?

665
00:25:01,692 --> 00:25:02,693
- Oh, dear.
- Hey.

666
00:25:02,760 --> 00:25:05,062
Read the room, train.

667
00:25:06,630 --> 00:25:07,665
- Sorry.
- No worries.

668
00:25:07,732 --> 00:25:09,200
What just happened?

669
00:25:09,467 --> 00:25:11,135
- I'm so sorry.
- Don't apologize.

670
00:25:12,103 --> 00:25:13,337
Shoot, I messed up big time.

671
00:25:13,404 --> 00:25:15,039
- Wipe your legs first.
- Are you guys okay?

672
00:25:15,272 --> 00:25:17,575
- I startled you, didn't I?
- Don't worry about it.

673
00:25:17,641 --> 00:25:19,310
When the trains come back

674
00:25:19,377 --> 00:25:21,445
I'll keep loading more sushi on them.

675
00:25:22,179 --> 00:25:23,481
This is an all-you-can-eat sushi bar.

676
00:25:24,615 --> 00:25:26,717
MASTER SUSHI CHEF
DOES NOT REST ONE MOMENT

677
00:25:26,784 --> 00:25:27,818
<i>Thank you for everything.</i>

678
00:25:28,519 --> 00:25:31,155
SUSHI TRAINS' ENDLESS JOURNEY

679
00:25:32,123 --> 00:25:34,892
PICKS ONE UP
BEFORE THE TRAIN GOES AWAY

680
00:25:34,959 --> 00:25:36,594
LOOKS GOOD

681
00:25:37,028 --> 00:25:38,996
A taste of Japan
in the heart of Gugi-dong.

682
00:25:39,797 --> 00:25:41,365
GASPS

683
00:25:42,333 --> 00:25:44,935
SORTS IT OUT BEFORE ANYONE NOTICES

684
00:25:46,003 --> 00:25:47,338
Next up is red-fleshed sushi.

685
00:25:47,738 --> 00:25:49,540
- Come on.
- Red-fleshed fish is the best.

686
00:25:51,308 --> 00:25:54,445
SLICE OF TUNA BELLY
WITH A MAJESTIC CRIMSON COLOR

687
00:25:55,079 --> 00:25:57,915
TUNA SUSHI IS DA-HEE'S FAVORITE

688
00:25:57,982 --> 00:25:59,050
That's a good one.

689
00:25:59,717 --> 00:26:02,820
THE TUNA SUSHI PIECE
IS NOW ON THE TRAIN

690
00:26:03,988 --> 00:26:05,723
MISSED IT

691
00:26:06,390 --> 00:26:08,893
SHE'S BEEN BUSY
ADMIRING KEUN-SUK'S WORK

692
00:26:09,226 --> 00:26:10,227
URGENTLY MOVES

693
00:26:10,294 --> 00:26:11,529
BUT MISSED THE SUSHI

694
00:26:11,595 --> 00:26:12,630
The train's coming back.

695
00:26:13,364 --> 00:26:15,132
- It's got great texture.
- Jae-hyeon...

696
00:26:15,199 --> 00:26:16,467
1 MORE TUNA SUSHI

697
00:26:18,569 --> 00:26:20,137
RELIEVED

698
00:26:20,204 --> 00:26:22,106
I'LL TAKE THAT

699
00:26:22,173 --> 00:26:23,707
Wait, no.

700
00:26:25,409 --> 00:26:26,644
She just stole your piece.

701
00:26:27,812 --> 00:26:29,313
- It's pretty fun.
- Who knew, right?

702
00:26:29,380 --> 00:26:30,548
- I had no idea.
- Wait, no.

703
00:26:32,183 --> 00:26:33,217
She just stole your piece.

704
00:26:33,717 --> 00:26:35,820
- Da-hee's been waiting for that.
- Really?

705
00:26:36,353 --> 00:26:37,888
We've got another one here.

706
00:26:37,955 --> 00:26:39,290
- It's coming your way.
- No worries.

707
00:26:39,356 --> 00:26:40,357
YOU CAN TAKE THIS!

708
00:26:40,791 --> 00:26:44,195
Let Da-hee have her tuna sushi.

709
00:26:44,261 --> 00:26:45,596
Remember that, Soo-jin.

710
00:26:45,663 --> 00:26:47,264
If she's eyeing something,
let her have it.

711
00:26:47,331 --> 00:26:49,433
You guys left it, so I thought...

712
00:26:49,500 --> 00:26:51,035
THAT'S ENOUGH, I'M EMBARRASSED AS IS

713
00:26:51,869 --> 00:26:53,237
- The owner's... So funny.
- It's good.

714
00:26:53,304 --> 00:26:54,872
Hey, your tuna sushi is here.

715
00:26:55,873 --> 00:26:57,374
GET HERE ALREADY

716
00:26:57,441 --> 00:26:58,576
- You've got yours.
- You can tell

717
00:26:58,642 --> 00:27:00,377
what piece
the next person's waiting for.

718
00:27:00,444 --> 00:27:02,947
EVEN WHEN THE SUSHI PARTY
HAPPENS IN YOUR OWN HOME

719
00:27:03,013 --> 00:27:05,516
THE FIRST-COME-FIRST-SERVED RULE
MUST BE FOLLOWED

720
00:27:05,583 --> 00:27:07,218
Da-hee's been eyeing that
the whole time.

721
00:27:07,284 --> 00:27:08,586
FINALLY GOT IT

722
00:27:10,154 --> 00:27:11,422
It's incredible.

723
00:27:11,489 --> 00:27:12,656
So hilarious.

724
00:27:13,157 --> 00:27:14,158
It tastes just right.

725
00:27:14,925 --> 00:27:16,093
Amazing.

726
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:17,495
Hey!

727
00:27:17,561 --> 00:27:19,563
- Is it good? Nice enough?
- For sure.

728
00:27:20,331 --> 00:27:22,266
FINALLY TRIES A PIECE
AFTER FEEDING HIS HOUSEMATES

729
00:27:22,333 --> 00:27:23,934
- How is it?
- Go ahead and eat.

730
00:27:24,535 --> 00:27:25,936
Why don't you take a seat, too?

731
00:27:26,003 --> 00:27:28,172
- You totally should.
- You can sit and enjoy now.

732
00:27:28,239 --> 00:27:30,441
- Dig in before it goes cold.
- Why don't we heat that up?

733
00:27:30,508 --> 00:27:31,675
It's still warm.

734
00:27:31,742 --> 00:27:34,145
- It's best when it's warm.
- Try it. It's good.

735
00:27:34,445 --> 00:27:35,679
I get why people love seasonal food.

736
00:27:35,746 --> 00:27:37,047
TRIES SOO-JIN'S SOYBEAN PASTE SOUP

737
00:27:37,114 --> 00:27:38,149
SATISFIED

738
00:27:39,016 --> 00:27:40,217
How cute.

739
00:27:40,284 --> 00:27:41,619
AS THE TRAINS RUN,
THEIR APPETITE GROWS

740
00:27:41,685 --> 00:27:44,155
- It's fun to watch.
- If anyone wants more soup

741
00:27:44,221 --> 00:27:45,222
please let me know.

742
00:27:46,157 --> 00:27:48,692
DO-YEON IS A PICKY EATER

743
00:27:48,759 --> 00:27:50,127
I guess it's going fast.

744
00:27:50,194 --> 00:27:53,464
BUT KEUN-SUK'S FINE SUSHI
HAS MANAGED TO CHARM HER, TOO

745
00:27:53,764 --> 00:27:56,267
A BIG BITE

746
00:27:56,634 --> 00:27:58,302
Thanks for all the work.

747
00:27:58,369 --> 00:27:59,370
SATISFIED

748
00:27:59,436 --> 00:28:00,538
It's really good.

749
00:28:02,673 --> 00:28:04,842
IT TAKES A GROUP
TO ENJOY THIS KIND OF FUN

750
00:28:04,909 --> 00:28:06,177
What are you guys doing tomorrow?

751
00:28:07,178 --> 00:28:08,279
I'm curious, too.

752
00:28:08,612 --> 00:28:10,981
Daniel and I had a chat

