Aren't we kind of late?

1487
00:56:38,282 --> 00:56:39,616
<i>- You know what?</i>
- Yeah?

1488
00:56:39,917 --> 00:56:41,151
<i>We're still at home.</i>

1489
00:56:41,218 --> 00:56:42,219
ACTUALLY A PRANK

1490
00:56:44,455 --> 00:56:46,690
Don't give me that nonsense, Do-yeon.

1491
00:56:46,757 --> 00:56:48,158
<i>Are you at the station?</i>

1492
00:56:48,225 --> 00:56:49,626
- Cut it out, okay?
<i>- Sorry.</i>

1493
00:56:49,693 --> 00:56:51,462
We're still at home
because we slept in.

1494
00:56:51,528 --> 00:56:52,830
ROUGH LANGUAGE
DOESN'T EVEN BOTHER THEM

1495
00:56:52,896 --> 00:56:53,998
<i>You slept in?</i>

1496
00:56:54,064 --> 00:56:57,101
I'll send you
the details of our tickets.

1497
00:56:57,167 --> 00:56:58,836
THE STRONGER THE FRIENDSHIP,
THE SILLIER THEY GET

1498
00:56:58,902 --> 00:57:01,038
Have fun, okay?

1499
00:57:03,273 --> 00:57:05,109
You both look nice, though.

1500
00:57:05,776 --> 00:57:07,378
SQUEALS

1501
00:57:07,611 --> 00:57:08,946
Seriously?

1502
00:57:09,346 --> 00:57:11,181
- You're really in your suit.
- You're still wearing it.

1503
00:57:11,248 --> 00:57:12,850
The event ran longer than planned

1504
00:57:12,916 --> 00:57:14,818
- so I had to dash to get here.
- Seriously?

1505
00:57:14,885 --> 00:57:17,521
- I hosted a wedding reception.
- Really?

1506
00:57:17,588 --> 00:57:19,089
What's inside your backpack?

1507
00:57:19,156 --> 00:57:21,992
I just packed a jacket
in case it gets cold.

1508
00:57:22,059 --> 00:57:23,994
- I have the beanie, too.
- What beanie?

1509
00:57:24,061 --> 00:57:26,330
- Our Thimble Trio beanie.
- You brought it?

1510
00:57:26,397 --> 00:57:28,766
- Honestly, that slipped our mind.
- Are you serious?

1511
00:57:28,832 --> 00:57:31,068
- You guys are unbelievable.
- Can you wear it, though?

1512
00:57:31,135 --> 00:57:33,070
On top of all this?

1513
00:57:33,137 --> 00:57:35,706
Come on, I'm wearing a suit.
You guys are the worst.

1514
00:57:35,773 --> 00:57:38,075
How could you forget your beanies?

1515
00:57:38,509 --> 00:57:40,110
- Unbelievable.
- You can wear it, though.

1516
00:57:40,177 --> 00:57:42,479
- You looked so good in your beanie.
- Hey, handsome.

1517
00:57:42,546 --> 00:57:43,614
You can wear it for the group.

1518
00:57:43,680 --> 00:57:44,681
HIS FRIENDS KNOW NO MERCY

1519
00:57:45,649 --> 00:57:47,217
- Let's get moving.
- Seriously, though.

1520
00:57:47,284 --> 00:57:49,386
I had a hectic afternoon.

1521
00:57:51,188 --> 00:57:54,324
Shouldn't we pick up
some snacks or something?

1522
00:57:54,391 --> 00:57:55,659
Da-hee brought hard-boiled eggs.

1523
00:57:55,726 --> 00:57:57,694
- I did.
- I brought soda as well.

1524
00:57:57,761 --> 00:57:58,762
What's with the high angle?

1525
00:57:58,829 --> 00:58:01,532
- This is trending among the MZs.
- All MZs do this.

1526
00:58:01,598 --> 00:58:03,767
We might end up
with no decent footage, though.

1527
00:58:08,005 --> 00:58:09,773
SLAPSTICK OUT OF THE BLUE

1528
00:58:10,808 --> 00:58:12,843
MASTER OF OLD-SCHOOL COMEDY
LIKE <i>NUMBER ONE HUMOR </i>STYLE JOKES

1529
00:58:13,377 --> 00:58:14,812
We're truly ancient

1530
00:58:14,878 --> 00:58:16,213
seeing how much we love this.

1531
00:58:16,914 --> 00:58:18,415
We love it because we're so old.

1532
00:58:18,482 --> 00:58:19,516
A TRIP DOWN MEMORY LANE BEGINS

1533
00:58:19,950 --> 00:58:22,686
We'll ride the rail bike
and go get Korean barbecue.

1534
00:58:22,753 --> 00:58:24,321
And t-that's your House Squad Goal?

1535
00:58:24,688 --> 00:58:26,957
- Yes, it's my goal.
- What's with the stuttering?

1536
00:58:27,024 --> 00:58:28,192
- Yes, it is.
- It's your thing?

1537
00:58:28,258 --> 00:58:29,259
Okay, got it.

1538
00:58:29,326 --> 00:58:30,494
CAN'T SAY NO TO HOUSE SQUAD GOALS

1539
00:58:30,561 --> 00:58:32,896
Do-yeon and I shared
this joke on our way.

1540
00:58:33,163 --> 00:58:34,164
Coincidentally

1541
00:58:34,231 --> 00:58:36,366
the 87ers and the 85ers
are spending the day separately

1542
00:58:36,433 --> 00:58:37,901
like we're having a competition.

1543
00:58:37,968 --> 00:58:39,470
Of course, it's not a competition

1544
00:58:39,536 --> 00:58:41,238
but I still told Do-yeon

1545
00:58:41,305 --> 00:58:42,306
to get hyped up.

1546
00:58:42,372 --> 00:58:43,540
- Get hyped up?
- Show me energy.

1547
00:58:43,607 --> 00:58:45,642
WE CAN'T LOSE TO THE 87ERS

1548
00:58:45,709 --> 00:58:46,910
What on earth?

1549
00:58:48,245 --> 00:58:49,413
- Daniel.
- Yeah?

1550
00:58:50,414 --> 00:58:52,015
What's that supposed to mean?

1551
00:58:52,082 --> 00:58:53,217
"You're awesome."

1552
00:58:53,283 --> 00:58:54,551
Why put your thumbs
behind your teeth?

1553
00:58:54,618 --> 00:58:55,819
- For the popping motion?
- Yeah.

1554
00:58:56,453 --> 00:58:57,788
- I see.
- Like popping a beer bottle.

1555
00:58:57,855 --> 00:58:58,956
"You're awesome."

1556
00:58:59,389 --> 00:59:01,158
- Not feeling it?
- I'll add the sound for you. Go.

1557
00:59:01,225 --> 00:59:02,226
CLICK

1558
00:59:02,893 --> 00:59:05,395
PERFECT PARTNERSHIP

1559
00:59:05,963 --> 00:59:07,364
- Pretty good, right?
- Not bad.

1560
00:59:07,431 --> 00:59:09,133
- Not bad at all.
- One more. One, two, three.

1561
00:59:09,199 --> 00:59:10,200
CLICK

1562
00:59:10,267 --> 00:59:11,335
CRACKING UP

1563
00:59:11,768 --> 00:59:13,837
THE 85ERS SHOULD GET
85 POINTS FOR GOOD CHEMISTRY

1564
00:59:13,904 --> 00:59:15,038
You guys are in good spirits.

1565
00:59:15,105 --> 00:59:16,106
- Here it is.
- All amped up.

1566
00:59:16,173 --> 00:59:18,308
- Now, let's depart for Chuncheon.
- Our train is here.

1567
00:59:18,375 --> 00:59:20,110
- Choo-choo.
- Here we go.

1568
00:59:20,177 --> 00:59:22,179
Hey, Chuncheon. Here we come.

1569
00:59:24,615 --> 00:59:26,483
THIS TRAIN IS HEADED TO CHUNCHEON

1570
00:59:27,151 --> 00:59:29,653
I'M SO EXCITED!

1571
00:59:30,287 --> 00:59:32,156
<i>We're on our way to Chuncheon.</i>

1572
00:59:32,222 --> 00:59:33,924
WE ARE USING PHOTOS
DUE TO LACK OF NECESSARY PERMIT

1573
00:59:34,224 --> 00:59:36,126
<i>Let's all put on</i>

1574
00:59:36,193 --> 00:59:38,095
<i>- an annoying face.</i>
<i>- Annoying face?</i>

1575
00:59:39,096 --> 00:59:43,667
THIS IS HOW PEOPLE IN THEIR FORTIES
HAVE FUN THESE DAYS

1576
00:59:43,734 --> 00:59:44,935
Patty-cake

1577
00:59:45,002 --> 00:59:47,070
A mad stray dog goes

1578
00:59:47,137 --> 00:59:49,039
Woof! Woof!

1579
00:59:49,540 --> 00:59:51,074
THIS TRIP HAS NO ROMANTIC CHARM

1580
00:59:51,141 --> 00:59:53,644
<i>I want to buy at least some snacks.</i>

1581
00:59:53,710 --> 00:59:57,147
<i>- Enough. Do you think you're a kid?</i>
<i>- Stop it. Why do you keep whining?</i>

1582
00:59:57,548 --> 00:59:59,383
<i>- Hey, you're glaring.</i>
<i>- Watch it, okay?</i>

1583
00:59:59,449 --> 01:00:01,618
<i>Don't glare at us.</i>

1584
01:00:01,685 --> 01:00:03,120
<i>I'll do as I please.</i>

1585
01:00:03,720 --> 01:00:05,088
<i>You're terrible.</i>

1586
01:00:05,489 --> 01:00:06,557
<i>So childish.</i>

1587
01:00:07,324 --> 01:00:09,259
<i>- Are you two having fun?</i>
<i>- I know I am.</i>

1588
01:00:09,326 --> 01:00:10,327
CHILDISHNESS OFF THE CHARTS

1589
01:00:10,394 --> 01:00:11,695
<i>- You know...</i>
<i>- Hey, it's Namchuncheon.</i>

1590
01:00:11,762 --> 01:00:14,464
<i>- This is our stop. Let's get off.</i>
<i>- We have to get off.</i>

1591
01:00:14,765 --> 01:00:16,466
<i>We got here faster than I thought.</i>

1592
01:00:17,334 --> 01:00:19,036
- It's cold.
- It's so cold.

1593
01:00:19,102 --> 01:00:20,437
- It's chilly.
- Totally.

1594
01:00:21,338 --> 01:00:22,673
Still, the weather's nice.

1595
01:00:24,374 --> 01:00:25,776
This is so nice.

1596
01:00:27,010 --> 01:00:28,679
It's pretty warm in the sun.

1597
01:00:28,745 --> 01:00:29,846
Chuncheon.

1598
01:00:29,913 --> 01:00:31,215
THIS IS JUST AS NICE
AS THE 87ER'S TRIP

1599
01:00:31,682 --> 01:00:32,716
DO-YEON BOOKED A CAR LAST NIGHT

1600
01:00:32,783 --> 01:00:34,585
All right. Let's go.

1601
01:00:35,652 --> 01:00:37,454
LET'S HAVE AS MUCH FUN
AS THE 87ERS DID!

1602
01:00:37,521 --> 01:00:38,722
All right.

1603
01:00:47,824 --> 01:00:48,992
WHO'S DRIVING?

1604
01:00:49,058 --> 01:00:50,326
Come on.

1605
01:00:50,660 --> 01:00:52,562
This isn't a self-driving vehicle.

1606
01:00:52,629 --> 01:00:53,997
- Let's go.
- Off we go.

1607
01:00:54,063 --> 01:00:55,698
- Let's go!
- Hang on.

1608
01:00:56,132 --> 01:00:58,568
- Here we go.
- All right!

1609
01:00:58,635 --> 01:01:01,104
ENERGY THROUGH THE ROOF

1610
01:01:01,171 --> 01:01:02,705
We're going to Chuncheon!

1611
01:01:02,772 --> 01:01:04,007
Chuncheon!

1612
01:01:04,073 --> 01:01:05,141
This is lovely.

1613
01:01:05,508 --> 01:01:06,709
Will there be a lot of traffic?

1614
01:01:07,310 --> 01:01:09,913
Oh, really? Please take us
to the rail bike park first.

1615
01:01:09,979 --> 01:01:11,714
Okay, thank you.

1616
01:01:11,781 --> 01:01:12,916
Let's hit the rail bike park.

1617
01:01:12,982 --> 01:01:13,983
- Are we going?
- Sure.

1618
01:01:14,050 --> 01:01:17,420
DANIEL WILL DRIVE
AND TAKE THEM TO THE RAIL BIKE PARK

1619
01:01:17,487 --> 01:01:18,488
Here we go now.

1620
01:01:18,555 --> 01:01:19,856
- Let's go!
- You know what?

1621
01:01:19,923 --> 01:01:22,025
<i>I'm stoked.</i>
<i>We're having so much fun already.</i>

1622
01:01:22,091 --> 01:01:23,526
<i>- My stomach hurts from laughing.</i>
<i>- This is great.</i>

1623
01:01:23,593 --> 01:01:24,928
THE 85ERS' TRIP
TO CHUNCHEON BEGINS NOW!

1624
01:01:24,994 --> 01:01:26,529
<i>This is exciting.</i>

1625
01:01:26,596 --> 01:01:31,134
87ERS, YOU RODE THE HELICOPTER

1626
01:01:31,201 --> 01:01:33,036
<i>Gosh, do you see this?</i>

1627
01:01:33,369 --> 01:01:35,672
<i>- "Gimyujeong..."</i>
<i>- "Gimyujeong Rail Bike."</i>

1628
01:01:35,738 --> 01:01:36,873
WE'RE RIDING A RAIL BIKE

1629
01:01:36,940 --> 01:01:38,007
All right, guys.

1630
01:01:38,074 --> 01:01:39,909
This is my first time
riding a rail bike.

1631
01:01:40,109 --> 01:01:41,244
It's your first time.

1632
01:01:42,078 --> 01:01:44,247
THIS IS TRULY ROMANTIC STUFF

1633
01:01:44,314 --> 01:01:45,882
This is Do-yeon's House Squad Goal.

1634
01:01:45,949 --> 01:01:47,417
Don't you want to sit up front?

1635
01:01:47,484 --> 01:01:49,419
MR. SUIT GETS ON BOARD, TOO

1636
01:01:50,053 --> 01:01:53,223
WE MIGHT NOT HAVE A PROPELLER,
BUT WE HAVE THREE PEDALERS

1637
01:01:53,289 --> 01:01:54,691
Hey, this is pretty nice.

1638
01:01:54,757 --> 01:01:57,193
SUPERIOR TO THE HELICOPTER
IN TERMS OF OPENNESS

1639
01:01:57,260 --> 01:01:58,428
DO-YEON'S FIRST HOUSE SQUAD GOAL
RIDING A RAIL BIKE

1640
01:01:58,495 --> 01:01:59,796
We're going downhill.

1641
01:02:01,231 --> 01:02:04,634
BUT WILL THIS BE ENJOYABLE
FOR PEOPLE IN THEIR FORTIES?

1642
01:02:04,701 --> 01:02:06,736
- It's so much fun!
- All right!

1643
01:02:07,604 --> 01:02:10,974
THEIR CHEERS ARE LOUDER
THAN ANY NOISE A PROPELLER CAN MAKE

1644
01:02:11,040 --> 01:02:12,275
Hey, we're going so fast.

1645
01:02:12,342 --> 01:02:14,310
- Let's go!
- Hey, we're going too fast!

1646
01:02:15,178 --> 01:02:17,881
RAW THRILL OF SPEED

1647
01:02:18,948 --> 01:02:20,416
ZOOMING BY

1648
01:02:21,751 --> 01:02:24,187
This is our supercar.

1649
01:02:24,554 --> 01:02:27,323
- Vroom, vroom.
- This is our L**b**ghini.

1650
01:02:27,924 --> 01:02:31,461
THEY'RE GOING AT A DIFFERENT SPEED
BUT HAVING A BLAST ALL THE SAME

1651
01:02:31,794 --> 01:02:33,129
THE 87ERS ARE NOT ON THEIR MIND

1652
01:02:33,196 --> 01:02:35,031
THAT'S NOT THE CASE AT ALL

1653
01:02:35,098 --> 01:02:36,232
My gosh.

1654
01:02:36,299 --> 01:02:37,734
Do-yeon, are you enjoying this?

1655
01:02:37,800 --> 01:02:39,936
- I'm honestly over the moon.
- You're happy?

1656
01:02:41,004 --> 01:02:42,672
SO HAPPY THAT SHE CAN'T EVEN
OPEN HER EYES

1657
01:02:42,739 --> 01:02:43,740
ACTUALLY, THAT'S ON THE WIND

1658
01:02:44,741 --> 01:02:45,842
IT'S PRETTY CHILLY

1659
01:02:45,909 --> 01:02:47,377
It's so refreshing.
We got our own convertible.

1660
01:02:47,443 --> 01:02:48,611
I know, right?

1661
01:02:48,678 --> 01:02:49,879
This is great.

1662
01:02:49,946 --> 01:02:51,414
HE WILL REMEMBER THIS FOREVER

1663
01:02:51,481 --> 01:02:53,616
A RAIL BIKE TOUR IN A SUIT
ON A CHILLY SPRING DAY

1664
01:02:54,417 --> 01:02:56,719
They're stuck
in the city's polluted air.

1665
01:02:56,786 --> 01:02:58,888
- We're here breathing clean air.
- So true.

1666
01:02:58,955 --> 01:03:02,392
But I can't really speak well.

1667
01:03:02,458 --> 01:03:04,127
The cold air is numbing my lips.

1668
01:03:04,694 --> 01:03:06,629
Da-hee isn't doing her fair share.

1669
01:03:07,530 --> 01:03:08,765
This is a proper workout.

1670
01:03:10,133 --> 01:03:11,234
FREE RIDER 2

1671
01:03:11,301 --> 01:03:13,369
The air is so refreshing and nice

1672
01:03:13,436 --> 01:03:15,238
but it feels
like my ears will fall off.

1673
01:03:15,305 --> 01:03:18,074
THE ICY WIND OF CHUNCHEON IN MARCH
IS MAKING MR. SUIT FAINT

1674
01:03:18,374 --> 01:03:19,375
<i>Watch out.</i>

1675
01:03:19,442 --> 01:03:21,210
By any chance,
are you slacking off too, Daniel?

1676
01:03:21,277 --> 01:03:22,745
Well, it's just that I'm freezing.

1677
01:03:22,812 --> 01:03:23,813
Is that right?

1678
01:03:23,880 --> 01:03:25,648
- You think I'd be warm and toasty?
- Well, no.

1679
01:03:26,015 --> 01:03:27,183
Really?

1680
01:03:27,250 --> 01:03:28,518
GIGGLES

1681
01:03:28,585 --> 01:03:30,119
Why is it getting harder?

1682
01:03:31,955 --> 01:03:33,222
My mind must be playing tricks.

1683
01:03:33,289 --> 01:03:34,524
SHE'S DOING THE HEAVY LIFTING

1684
01:03:35,692 --> 01:03:36,693
Hang on.

1685
01:03:38,094 --> 01:03:42,065
IS HE PLACING A HEAT PACK
BEHIND DO-YEON'S NECK?

1686
01:03:43,900 --> 01:03:45,935
- What are you doing?
- What's going on?

1687
01:03:46,002 --> 01:03:47,203
Hey, that's hot.

1688
01:03:47,270 --> 01:03:48,304
It's just...

1689
01:03:50,106 --> 01:03:52,175
The hood of your top
is covering up my camera.

1690
01:03:52,241 --> 01:03:53,710
Seriously, you're the worst!

1691
01:03:54,377 --> 01:03:55,812
THE CAMERA IS NOT CAPTURING MY FACE

1692
01:03:56,346 --> 01:03:58,648
- I'll sit like this, okay?
- You're hilarious.

1693
01:03:58,948 --> 01:04:00,350
Are you satisfied?

1694
01:04:01,284 --> 01:04:02,585
It's okay. You can sit back.

1695
01:04:02,919 --> 01:04:04,220
I was just messing with you.

1696
01:04:04,287 --> 01:04:06,189
If you could only get the hood...

1697
01:04:06,255 --> 01:04:08,291
You get what I mean, right?

1698
01:04:08,358 --> 01:04:09,859
Just keep your hood out of the way.

1699
01:04:10,293 --> 01:04:11,427
Just the hood?

1700
01:04:11,494 --> 01:04:13,429
JUST SPEECHLESS

1701
01:04:13,997 --> 01:04:14,998
LOOKS AROUND

1702
01:04:15,064 --> 01:04:17,233
Guys, look at the tunnel around us.

1703
01:04:17,300 --> 01:04:18,334
It's so pretty.

1704
01:04:18,401 --> 01:04:19,435
A TUNNEL WITH ROMANTIC DECOR

1705
01:04:19,502 --> 01:04:20,703
- What's with the plants?
- This is unreal.

1706
01:04:20,770 --> 01:04:22,405
This is spicing things up.

1707
01:04:23,773 --> 01:04:25,942
They added lighting
to the reed patches here.

1708
01:04:26,476 --> 01:04:27,810
How romantic.

1709
01:04:27,877 --> 01:04:29,078
It's so cold.

1710
01:04:29,145 --> 01:04:30,513
Are your lips okay?

1711
01:04:30,580 --> 01:04:32,649
- Mine are so numb.
- I can't talk properly either.

1712
01:04:32,715 --> 01:04:33,950
- Right?
- My lips are numb

1713
01:04:34,017 --> 01:04:35,485
- and so are my ears.
- Yeah.

1714
01:04:36,519 --> 01:04:37,654
GOING EXTRA FAST

1715
01:04:37,720 --> 01:04:39,922
I can't feel my ears.

1716
01:04:41,391 --> 01:04:44,961
We're not exactly
enjoying the view here.

1717
01:04:45,028 --> 01:04:46,362
It's more like...

1718
01:04:46,829 --> 01:04:48,998
- We're trying to tackle a chore.
- We're so funny.

1719
01:04:49,065 --> 01:04:50,733
We're approaching a photo zone.

1720
01:04:50,800 --> 01:04:52,935
- It's right ahead of us.
- Where?

1721
01:04:53,002 --> 01:04:54,637
What kind of pose are we going for?

1722
01:04:54,704 --> 01:04:55,972
Something cute, nonchalant, or cool?

1723
01:04:56,039 --> 01:04:57,440
- I vote nonchalant.
- Nonchalant?

1724
01:04:58,541 --> 01:05:00,276
MASKS OF NONCHALANCE

1725
01:05:00,343 --> 01:05:02,445
BUT THEIR LEGS ARE SUPER-ENGAGED

1726
01:05:02,945 --> 01:05:05,848
ALMOST LIKE THE FRANTIC PADDLING
OF ELEGANT SWANS

1727
01:05:07,617 --> 01:05:08,851
All right. Let's go.

1728
01:05:08,918 --> 01:05:10,053
- Let's get going!
- Let's speed things up.

1729
01:05:10,119 --> 01:05:11,120
Let's go.

1730
01:05:11,187 --> 01:05:12,355
GOSH, IT'S SO COLD

1731
01:05:12,422 --> 01:05:14,590
WE'RE ON THE SAME PAGE, AREN'T WE?

1732
01:05:15,091 --> 01:05:17,226
FORGET ABOUT ROMANTIC TOUR
AND FOCUS ON PEDALING

1733
01:05:17,293 --> 01:05:18,294
It's just...

1734
01:05:18,728 --> 01:05:21,197
ALL ON THE SAME PAGE,
FURIOUSLY PEDALING AS ONE

1735
01:05:21,431 --> 01:05:22,565
<i>We didn't realize this before.</i>

1736
01:05:22,632 --> 01:05:24,701
<i>As it turns out,</i>
<i>all three of us are hotheads</i>

1737
01:05:24,967 --> 01:05:27,570
who must cross the finish line
as quickly as we can.

1738
01:05:27,804 --> 01:05:28,838
We were like

1739
01:05:28,905 --> 01:05:30,506
- "Let's be done with this."
- Like racehorses.

1740
01:05:30,573 --> 01:05:31,808
We had our blinkers on, so to speak.

1741
01:05:32,008 --> 01:05:34,210
We were like racehorses.
We didn't care for sightseeing.

1742
01:05:34,577 --> 01:05:35,645
We just raced ahead.

1743
01:05:36,379 --> 01:05:37,714
<i>We shared the mindset</i>

1744
01:05:37,780 --> 01:05:39,215
<i>that we needed</i>
<i>to finish this task quickly.</i>

1745
01:05:40,316 --> 01:05:41,317
SIGHS

1746
01:05:41,384 --> 01:05:42,952
LAUGHS

1747
01:05:43,086 --> 01:05:46,089
THEY DREAMED OF A ROMANTIC TRIP
AND FOUND THEMSELVES IN A BOOT CAMP

1748
01:05:46,155 --> 01:05:48,291
Hey, it's getting harder to pedal.

1749
01:05:48,357 --> 01:05:49,492
CHECKS

1750
01:05:49,559 --> 01:05:50,727
Are you guys pedaling?

1751
01:05:51,294 --> 01:05:54,063
Of course.
I've never stopped pedaling.

1752
01:05:54,130 --> 01:05:56,099
We've slowed down a bit, that's all.

1753
01:05:56,165 --> 01:05:58,601
- We're still...
- We're still pedaling.

1754
01:05:59,235 --> 01:06:01,304
We've got a steep climb up ahead.

1755
01:06:01,370 --> 01:06:03,072
My back hurts.

1756
01:06:03,439 --> 01:06:05,141
- What? Is music playing?
- They're playing music?

1757
01:06:05,208 --> 01:06:06,642
- Gosh.
- What's this?

1758
01:06:06,709 --> 01:06:08,945
It helps to cheer up the riders.

1759
01:06:09,011 --> 01:06:10,079
TUNNEL OF PUMP-UP SONG

1760
01:06:10,980 --> 01:06:13,516
TRUE STAMINA COMES FROM THE MIND

1761
01:06:14,150 --> 01:06:17,386
HYPING THEMSELVES UP
UNTIL THE VERY LAST MOMENT

1762
01:06:17,720 --> 01:06:18,721
ARE YOU WATCHING, 87ERS?

1763
01:06:18,788 --> 01:06:20,323
WE'RE HAVING SO MUCH FUN!

1764
01:06:22,725 --> 01:06:24,961
THEY ARE SQUEEZING OUT
EVERY LAST DROP OF ENERGY

1765
01:06:25,027 --> 01:06:26,829
Feels like we need a whistle.

1766
01:06:27,830 --> 01:06:29,565
MIMICS TRUMPET SOUNDS

1767
01:06:31,768 --> 01:06:35,505
THE 85ERS LET THEIR SENSE OF RIVALRY
WITH THE 87ERS GO TOO FAR

1768
01:06:36,305 --> 01:06:39,008
ABSOLUTELY DRAINED

1769
01:06:39,075 --> 01:06:41,444
IT'S TIME TO GO GET DINNER

1770
01:06:42,278 --> 01:06:43,379
<i>Do you guys know</i>

1771
01:06:43,446 --> 01:06:45,448
<i>that we finished the 40-minute course</i>
<i>in just 15 minutes?</i>

1772
01:06:46,282 --> 01:06:47,884
LAUGHS

1773
01:06:47,950 --> 01:06:50,052
<i>I hope you guys enjoyed it,</i>
<i>at the very least.</i>

1774
01:06:50,119 --> 01:06:51,254
<i>I had fun.</i>

1775
01:06:51,320 --> 01:06:53,723
<i>- It was the best day so far for me.</i>
<i>- Really?</i>

1776
01:06:54,090 --> 01:06:55,958
Our last stop today

1777
01:06:56,025 --> 01:06:57,794
is a restaurant
my friend recommended.

1778
01:06:57,860 --> 01:06:59,829
- Is it a great place, then?
- I hear it's incredible.

1779
01:06:59,896 --> 01:07:01,264
- Really?
- Really?

1780
01:07:01,330 --> 01:07:02,799
Wow, they serve sirloin bulgogi.

1781
01:07:03,332 --> 01:07:04,467
I hear it's amazing.

1782
01:07:04,934 --> 01:07:06,068
Sounds excellent.

1783
01:07:06,135 --> 01:07:08,204
It has the vibe
of a famous restaurant.

1784
01:07:09,605 --> 01:07:12,074
- There are so many autographs.
- Tons of celebrities have been here.

1785
01:07:12,141 --> 01:07:14,844
ONE OF THE BEST EATS IN CHUNCHEON
AS CAN BE SEEN FROM THE AUTOGRAPHS

1786
01:07:14,911 --> 01:07:16,112
I guess this is a famous place.

1787
01:07:16,179 --> 01:07:17,246
Must be.

1788
01:07:17,947 --> 01:07:19,382
Hey, that's Soo-jin's autograph.

1789
01:07:20,750 --> 01:07:22,885
<i>- What the... She knows this place?</i>
<i>- Guess she's been here.</i>

1790
01:07:22,952 --> 01:07:23,986
<i>Pretty cool, right?</i>

1791
01:07:24,921 --> 01:07:26,389
- I hear
- Yes.

1792
01:07:26,455 --> 01:07:28,624
- Is someone coming?
- the beef neck chain is to die for.

1793
01:07:29,759 --> 01:07:31,828
THE 87ERS TRIED BEEF TONGUE

1794
01:07:31,894 --> 01:07:35,398
AND AROUSED
THE 85ERS' COMPETITIVE STREAK

1795
01:07:36,399 --> 01:07:38,034
Was this sirloin?

1796
01:07:38,401 --> 01:07:40,436
- That's the neck chain.
- So that's the neck chain?

1797
01:07:40,503 --> 01:07:41,504
NECK CHAIN TO RECOVER STAMINA

1798
01:07:41,571 --> 01:07:42,805
This looks great.

1799
01:07:42,872 --> 01:07:44,540
- I hear the meat here is to die for.
- Really?

1800
01:07:44,841 --> 01:07:45,842
All right.

1801
01:07:45,908 --> 01:07:47,410
How do you like your beef?
On the rare side?

1802
01:07:47,476 --> 01:07:48,711
- A bit on the rare side.
- Me too.

1803
01:07:48,778 --> 01:07:50,913
- You can have this.
- Feel free to cook yours thoroughly.

1804
01:07:50,980 --> 01:07:52,715
- Yeah, you can do that.
- I'll let them cook a bit.

1805
01:07:53,249 --> 01:07:55,318
- Thanks, Daniel.
- We'll enjoy them.

1806
01:07:56,452 --> 01:07:58,754
Is it good?

1807
01:07:59,522 --> 01:08:01,057
- Is it good?
- It melts in your mouth.

1808
01:08:01,123 --> 01:08:02,325
- It does?
- For real.

1809
01:08:02,992 --> 01:08:04,393
This is incredible.

1810
01:08:04,927 --> 01:08:06,429
It's so good.

1811
01:08:06,495 --> 01:08:07,763
- Gosh.
- Isn't it amazing?

1812
01:08:07,830 --> 01:08:09,098
- It's great even without seasoning.
- Isn't it good?

1813
01:08:09,165 --> 01:08:10,166
<i>Right?</i>

1814
01:08:10,233 --> 01:08:11,467
KOREANS SHOULD SAVOR KOREAN BEEF

1815
01:08:11,534 --> 01:08:13,502
<i>Here are our photo zone photos.</i>

1816
01:08:13,569 --> 01:08:14,570
All right.

1817
01:08:16,706 --> 01:08:17,940
It looks like someone slapped me.

1818
01:08:18,007 --> 01:08:19,408
What's with you, Do-yeon?

1819
01:08:19,475 --> 01:08:21,878
<i>- You look like Rodin's work.</i>
<i>- That's me posing</i>

1820
01:08:21,944 --> 01:08:24,113
<i>but I look so worried.</i>

1821
01:08:24,180 --> 01:08:25,181
BUT WE ARE REALLY HAVING FUN

1822
01:08:25,248 --> 01:08:26,449
Who wants one?

1823
01:08:26,515 --> 01:08:28,718
THERE ARE ONLY TWO PHOTOS

1824
01:08:28,918 --> 01:08:29,986
Come on, guys.

1825
01:08:30,519 --> 01:08:31,721
Why don't you want one?

1826
01:08:31,787 --> 01:08:33,122
Let's do rock-paper-scissors
and have the losers take them.

1827
01:08:33,189 --> 01:08:34,190
Let's do that.

1828
01:08:34,257 --> 01:08:35,791
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

1829
01:08:36,525 --> 01:08:38,094
DA-HEE AND DANIEL WON THE PHOTOS

1830
01:08:39,195 --> 01:08:41,464
You took your time only to use rock?

1831
01:08:42,231 --> 01:08:43,966
And what happened
to "Rock, paper, scissors"?

1832
01:08:44,033 --> 01:08:46,102
Who says, "One, two, three"?

1833
01:08:46,535 --> 01:08:48,037
YOU DUMMIES

1834
01:08:48,371 --> 01:08:50,873
You should've said,
"Rock, paper, scissors."

1835
01:08:51,741 --> 01:08:53,576
Who counts for this game?

1836
01:08:53,643 --> 01:08:55,211
YET AGAIN,
THEY WERE SO EAGER TO WRAP THINGS UP

1837
01:08:56,212 --> 01:08:58,981
- What was that?
- We just couldn't be bothered...

1838
01:08:59,048 --> 01:09:01,183
ALMOST RUNNING ON EMPTY
AFTER SQUEEZING OUT ALL ENERGY

1839
01:09:01,250 --> 01:09:02,985
WE'RE EXHAUSTED

1840
01:09:03,052 --> 01:09:04,520
- Seriously, though.
- My abs.

1841
01:09:04,587 --> 01:09:07,089
How could you, guys?
This is our first memory together.

1842
01:09:07,156 --> 01:09:08,858
Why is it such a mess?

1843
01:09:09,258 --> 01:09:10,826
Still, this grows on you.

1844
01:09:10,893 --> 01:09:12,361
- You bet.
- Yeah, I like it.

1845
01:09:12,428 --> 01:09:14,030
The photo does grow on you.

1846
01:09:14,096 --> 01:09:15,798
- It's not bad.
- Of course not.

1847
01:09:16,198 --> 01:09:18,200
Daniel, are you shy around strangers?

1848
01:09:18,834 --> 01:09:20,369
- I'm shy around strangers.
- You are?

1849
01:09:20,436 --> 01:09:21,637
- But...
- Yes?

1850
01:09:22,204 --> 01:09:24,040
You know how some people

1851
01:09:24,106 --> 01:09:27,009
can't stand silence?

1852
01:09:27,076 --> 01:09:28,110
I'm not like that.

1853
01:09:28,177 --> 01:09:29,545
I actually enjoy silence.

1854
01:09:30,313 --> 01:09:31,414
So you're at ease

1855
01:09:31,480 --> 01:09:33,349
even when you're surrounded
by strangers.

1856
01:09:33,416 --> 01:09:34,617
- I never knew.
- He's delicate.

1857
01:09:34,684 --> 01:09:36,052
Totally.

1858
01:09:36,352 --> 01:09:38,688
- You notice details others miss.
- Yeah.

1859
01:09:39,722 --> 01:09:41,691
I noticed your crooked lips, too.

1860
01:09:42,625 --> 01:09:44,060
My lips are not crooked.

1861
01:09:44,126 --> 01:09:46,329
- Hey, that was pretty good.
- Good job.

1862
01:09:46,629 --> 01:09:47,797
So articulate, too.

1863
01:09:47,863 --> 01:09:49,632
My lips are not crooked at all.

1864
01:09:49,699 --> 01:09:51,334
Fine, your lips are not crooked.

1865
01:09:51,400 --> 01:09:53,336
You guys have an amazing skill.

1866
01:09:53,769 --> 01:09:55,705
Don't tick me off
with the crooked lips nonsense.

1867
01:09:55,771 --> 01:09:57,373
Fine, your lips are not crooked.

1868
01:09:57,440 --> 01:09:58,541
Do-yeon's lips are not crooked.

1869
01:09:58,607 --> 01:10:00,009
Wow, just how are you...

1870
01:10:01,110 --> 01:10:02,378
How are you doing that?

1871
01:10:02,845 --> 01:10:05,181
- You have great facial control.
- Yes, totally.

1872
01:10:05,247 --> 01:10:06,248
- You think so?
- Sure.

1873
01:10:06,816 --> 01:10:09,852
ALL HE NEEDS NOW IS THE ABILITY
TO FILTER HIS THOUGHTS

1874
01:10:09,919 --> 01:10:11,020
By the way

1875
01:10:11,287 --> 01:10:12,989
do you guys remember

1876
01:10:13,055 --> 01:10:15,391
how the 87ers sent us photos
of the barbecue on their Japan trip?

1877
01:10:15,458 --> 01:10:16,993
- Oh, right.
- I sure remember.

1878
01:10:17,059 --> 01:10:19,595
- But we didn't even...
- We should've sent some, too.

1879
01:10:19,662 --> 01:10:21,063
I guess we were starving.

1880
01:10:21,130 --> 01:10:23,165
We were totally focused,
like when we did the rail bike.

1881
01:10:23,232 --> 01:10:25,167
- We wolfed everything down.
- We're intense like that.

1882
01:10:26,035 --> 01:10:29,171
Our life experiences
hardened us this way.

1883
01:10:30,206 --> 01:10:31,207
Should I call Jae-hyeon?

1884
01:10:31,273 --> 01:10:32,274
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1885
01:10:33,209 --> 01:10:35,211
<i>- Hello?</i>
- Hey, Jae-hyeon.

1886
01:10:35,277 --> 01:10:37,913
<i>- Hi, Daniel.</i>
- Did you guys... What?

1887
01:10:37,980 --> 01:10:39,415
<i>We haven't had dinner yet.</i>

1888
01:10:39,482 --> 01:10:41,183
- You haven't?
<i>- No.</i>

1889
01:10:41,250 --> 01:10:43,119
Go ahead and eat already.

1890
01:10:43,519 --> 01:10:45,254
<i>- When are you guys coming back?</i>
- What?

1891
01:10:45,321 --> 01:10:47,289
- It will take us hours.
- We won't be home anytime soon.

1892
01:10:47,356 --> 01:10:50,326
Your dinner will be too late
if you wait for us.

1893
01:10:50,393 --> 01:10:52,128
<i>- I didn't mean to share this...</i>
- What is it?

1894
01:10:53,362 --> 01:10:57,433
- What's up?
<i>- We have a new cast member.</i>

1895
01:10:57,500 --> 01:10:58,934
<i>- A new member joined us.</i>
- Who?

1896
01:10:59,001 --> 01:11:00,669
<i>I didn't want to startle you...</i>

1897
01:11:00,736 --> 01:11:01,771
Who is it?

1898
01:11:01,837 --> 01:11:03,706
<i>See for yourselves.</i>
<i>I'm sure you'll be delighted.</i>

1899
01:11:15,273 --> 01:11:17,975
Is it a guy or a girl?

1900
01:11:19,510 --> 01:11:21,045
- That's so cringe.
<i>- It's a guy.</i>

1901
01:11:21,112 --> 01:11:23,047
- We'll be there.
- We're on our way.

1902
01:11:23,114 --> 01:11:24,248
- See you soon.
<i>- Okay.</i>

1903
01:11:24,315 --> 01:11:26,083
- We'll be there in a flash.
- See you.

1904
01:11:26,150 --> 01:11:27,218
Unbelievable.

1905
01:11:27,552 --> 01:11:28,786
We've got to go.

1906
01:11:28,853 --> 01:11:30,388
Get the bill, Do-yeon.

1907
01:11:30,955 --> 01:11:31,956
- Hey.
- Ouch.

1908
01:11:32,690 --> 01:11:34,091
FORGET ABOUT FRIENDSHIP

1909
01:11:34,158 --> 01:11:36,627
WHO CARES ABOUT THAT?

1910
01:11:38,796 --> 01:11:40,731
THIS GUY HAS BEEN DISCARDED
IN A FLASH

1911
01:11:41,299 --> 01:11:43,434
CUTTING TIES AS QUICKLY
AS THEY FINISHED THE RAIL BIKE COURSE

1912
01:11:43,501 --> 01:11:45,570
You two are just unbelievable.

1913
01:11:45,636 --> 01:11:48,072
- So childish.
- We were just messing with you.

1914
01:11:48,139 --> 01:11:50,841
Why would we need anyone else
when we have you?

1915
01:11:51,609 --> 01:11:54,478
- Does that mean we have a guest?
- Beats me.

1916
01:11:54,545 --> 01:11:56,180
But if someone is visiting

1917
01:11:56,881 --> 01:11:59,383
our place at this hour

1918
01:11:59,450 --> 01:12:00,751
he's got too much time on his hands.

1919
01:12:02,353 --> 01:12:03,888
- Way too much time.
- It's the weekends.

1920
01:12:03,955 --> 01:12:06,857
- It's precious time.
- He has no friends to hang out with.

1921
01:12:07,124 --> 01:12:08,693
- Let's go.
- Okay.

1922
01:12:09,060 --> 01:12:10,928
<i>- Loved the dinner.</i>
<i>- Let's go.</i>

1923
01:12:10,995 --> 01:12:13,130
THAT'S IT FOR DO-YEON'S
NOT-SO-ROMANTIC ROMANTIC TRIP

1924
01:12:13,197 --> 01:12:15,466
<i>Give me a kiss,</i>
<i>and I'll give you a banana.</i>

1925
01:12:15,533 --> 01:12:16,667
<i>A kiss, please.</i>

1926
01:12:17,201 --> 01:12:18,402
<i>Come on, a peck.</i>

1927
01:12:19,103 --> 01:12:21,205
SOO-JIN IS BEGGING FOR A KISS
FROM A MYSTERY MALE GUEST

1928
01:12:21,272 --> 01:12:22,607
Come on, a peck.

1929
01:12:22,673 --> 01:12:23,808
Give me a kiss here.

1930
01:12:24,075 --> 01:12:25,943
WHY IS A TODDLER HERE?

1931
01:12:26,010 --> 01:12:27,278
Open wide.

1932
01:12:27,878 --> 01:12:29,180
Take a bite. My gosh.

1933
01:12:29,246 --> 01:12:30,748
Did I give him too much?

1934
01:12:30,815 --> 01:12:33,017
MUNCH, MUNCH

1935
01:12:33,351 --> 01:12:35,486
WHAT'S GOING ON?

1936
01:12:35,553 --> 01:12:38,489
STIFF AS A BOARD

1937
01:12:38,689 --> 01:12:40,091
I need hot broth.

1938
01:12:40,625 --> 01:12:41,892
Goodness.

1939
01:12:42,760 --> 01:12:43,928
- We're home.
- Gosh.

1940
01:12:43,995 --> 01:12:44,996
It's so warm here.

1941
01:12:45,062 --> 01:12:46,063
We're home at last.

1942
01:12:46,130 --> 01:12:47,264
I want some <i>ramyeon.</i>

1943
01:12:47,832 --> 01:12:48,833
What on earth?

1944
01:12:48,899 --> 01:12:49,900
What's the matter?

1945
01:12:52,770 --> 01:12:55,106
DUMBSTRUCK

1946
01:12:55,172 --> 01:12:56,941
- What?
- What's with the fences?

1947
01:12:58,643 --> 01:13:00,511
SOMEONE SET UP FENCES?

1948
01:13:00,578 --> 01:13:03,247
BUT THESE WEREN'T HERE WHEN THEY LEFT

1949
01:13:04,515 --> 01:13:05,850
WHILE THEY WERE AWAY

1950
01:13:05,916 --> 01:13:07,551
SOMEONE MADE CHANGES TO THEIR HOME

1951
01:13:07,618 --> 01:13:10,021
- What happened?
- Where are our couch and stuff?

1952
01:13:11,155 --> 01:13:13,991
WHAT ON EARTH HAS HAPPENED?

1953
01:13:14,058 --> 01:13:15,059
IS IT THE OTHER GIRLS' DOING?

1954
01:13:15,126 --> 01:13:17,261
Only the living room was changed.
The other rooms are as is.

1955
01:13:17,928 --> 01:13:20,031
Why did they set these up?

1956
01:13:20,631 --> 01:13:22,166
What are these for?

1957
01:13:23,267 --> 01:13:24,435
THE DOORBELL RINGS

1958
01:13:24,502 --> 01:13:25,503
Who is it?

1959
01:13:26,070 --> 01:13:27,371
Hey, hang on a second!

1960
01:13:27,805 --> 01:13:28,873
- I'll get the door.
- What?

1961
01:13:29,640 --> 01:13:30,908
Who is it?

1962
01:13:35,546 --> 01:13:37,381
GASPS

1963
01:13:37,882 --> 01:13:40,051
BACKS AWAY

1964
01:13:40,117 --> 01:13:42,319
SNEAKS A PEEK

1965
01:13:43,320 --> 01:13:45,122
AT THE SIGHT OF UNEXPECTED GUESTS

1966
01:13:45,189 --> 01:13:48,259
HIS MIND GOES BLANK

1967
01:13:48,926 --> 01:13:50,728
- Hello.
- Hi.

1968
01:13:51,162 --> 01:13:53,097
Hello.

1969
01:13:53,397 --> 01:13:55,266
- Hi, come here.
- Here he is.

1970
01:13:55,499 --> 01:13:57,401
Say, "Hello, Uncle Keun-suk."

1971
01:13:57,468 --> 01:13:58,602
- Who is this?
- What's going on?

1972
01:13:58,669 --> 01:13:59,837
Let's go inside.

1973
01:13:59,904 --> 01:14:01,272
- Who is this?
- What's going on?

1974
01:14:01,338 --> 01:14:02,406
Let's go inside.

1975
01:14:03,107 --> 01:14:06,711
SHOCKED

1976
01:14:07,078 --> 01:14:09,246
It's cold out here. Come on in.

1977
01:14:09,313 --> 01:14:10,514
Gosh, this way.

1978
01:14:10,581 --> 01:14:13,317
It's cold outside.
Why don't I take you in?

1979
01:14:14,719 --> 01:14:15,953
- You cutie.
- Look at his cheeks.

1980
01:14:16,253 --> 01:14:17,488
Hello, come here.

1981
01:14:17,555 --> 01:14:18,622
Say, "Hello, Aunt Soo-jin."

1982
01:14:18,689 --> 01:14:19,957
Come to me.

1983
01:14:20,024 --> 01:14:21,992
He wants me to hold him.

1984
01:14:22,059 --> 01:14:23,127
Here.

1985
01:14:23,194 --> 01:14:24,695
WHOSE BABY IS THIS?

1986
01:14:25,896 --> 01:14:28,365
Parenting was
among your House Squad Goals.

1987
01:14:28,632 --> 01:14:29,633
Whose was it?

1988
01:14:30,167 --> 01:14:33,337
SOMEONE MENTIONED PARENTING
AS THEIR HOUSE SQUAD GOAL?

1989
01:14:33,871 --> 01:14:35,539
THE RULE IN GUGI-DONG HOUSE DEMANDS

1990
01:14:35,606 --> 01:14:37,141
SUPPORT FOR EACH OTHER'S
HOUSE SQUAD GOAL

1991
01:14:37,208 --> 01:14:40,211
THEY MUST PARTICIPATE IN THE PROJECT,
NO QUESTION ASKED

1992
01:14:40,578 --> 01:14:42,513
STILL, EVERYONE IS SINGLE

1993
01:14:42,580 --> 01:14:43,714
Please take good care of him.

1994
01:14:43,781 --> 01:14:45,082
I brought lots of his things here.

1995
01:14:45,449 --> 01:14:47,852
- I'll put them in here.
- Why don't we go inside?

1996
01:14:50,154 --> 01:14:51,255
Look.

1997
01:14:51,322 --> 01:14:53,390
PLEASE TAKE CARE OF HIM
UNTIL HIS MOTHER CLOCKS OUT

1998
01:14:53,457 --> 01:14:54,792
Want to look around?

1999
01:14:54,859 --> 01:14:56,260
15-MONTH-OLD
CHO GYU-JIN

2000
01:14:56,327 --> 01:14:57,495
Can you guess what this is?

2001
01:14:57,561 --> 01:14:58,629
IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU, EVERYONE

2002
01:14:59,163 --> 01:15:00,331
Do you want to go down?

2003
01:15:00,765 --> 01:15:01,799
Want to stand on the floor?

2004
01:15:01,866 --> 01:15:02,867
SOO-JIN CARES FOR GYU-JIN

2005
01:15:02,933 --> 01:15:04,702
There we go. Let me get your shoes.

2006
01:15:04,769 --> 01:15:07,838
IN THE MEANTIME,
KEUN-SUK IS HAVING A BREAKDOWN

2007
01:15:08,339 --> 01:15:11,108
DUMBFOUNDED BY THE SURPRISE GUEST

2008
01:15:11,175 --> 01:15:12,877
Gosh, you're a cutie.

2009
01:15:13,811 --> 01:15:17,214
AN EXPERIENCED NANNY
WASHES HER HANDS FIRST

2010
01:15:17,281 --> 01:15:18,349
AND GOES INTO NANNY MODE

2011
01:15:18,415 --> 01:15:19,483
Want to check this out?

2012
01:15:20,785 --> 01:15:22,987
Hang on. I'll go get a banana.

2013
01:15:23,053 --> 01:15:24,688
THIS NEWBIE IS STILL IN DENIAL

2014
01:15:24,755 --> 01:15:25,956
Give me a kiss

2015
01:15:26,023 --> 01:15:27,491
and I'll give you a banana.

2016
01:15:27,558 --> 01:15:28,559
A kiss, please.

2017
01:15:29,026 --> 01:15:30,528
EXPERT NANNY

2018
01:15:30,594 --> 01:15:32,029
Give me a kiss here.

2019
01:15:32,363 --> 01:15:34,765
EXCITED

2020
01:15:35,099 --> 01:15:37,234
SIMPLY AMAZED

2021
01:15:37,668 --> 01:15:39,537
IN OBSERVATION MODE
FROM THE SIDELINES

2022
01:15:39,603 --> 01:15:41,739
EYES WANDER IN PANIC

2023
01:15:42,306 --> 01:15:43,874
PLEASE HURRY

2024
01:15:43,941 --> 01:15:45,209
Open wide.

2025
01:15:45,776 --> 01:15:47,111
Take a bite. My gosh.

2026
01:15:47,178 --> 01:15:48,612
Did I give him too much?

2027
01:15:48,679 --> 01:15:50,915
CHEEKS BULGING

2028
01:15:50,981 --> 01:15:52,016
He's eating fine.

2029
01:15:54,819 --> 01:15:55,820
LATE TO THE SCENE

2030
01:15:55,886 --> 01:15:58,289
Bite into it. There you go.

2031
01:15:59,590 --> 01:16:03,060
THIS IS NOT A FREEZE-FRAME

2032
01:16:04,094 --> 01:16:06,096
It's so delicious, isn't it?

2033
01:16:06,664 --> 01:16:10,835
WHAT IS GOING ON?

2034
01:16:11,202 --> 01:16:14,138
WHY IS A TODDLER
EATING A BANANA IN OUR HOME?

2035
01:16:15,439 --> 01:16:17,942
HE'S ENJOYING EVERY BITE OF THAT

2036
01:16:18,008 --> 01:16:19,009
Bite into it.

2037
01:16:19,076 --> 01:16:21,679
GET IN HERE ALREADY

2038
01:16:23,113 --> 01:16:24,148
Why...

2039
01:16:24,215 --> 01:16:26,183
ANXIOUSLY JOINS THE PARENTING PARTY

2040
01:16:26,817 --> 01:16:30,254
SOMEONE ASKED FOR A PARENTING SESSION

2041
01:16:30,321 --> 01:16:35,693
WHO WAS IT?

2042
01:16:36,026 --> 01:16:38,062
IT WAS ME

2043
01:16:38,128 --> 01:16:40,831
I didn't think you'd pull it off.

2044
01:16:40,898 --> 01:16:43,367
You guys asked me about my ideas
for House Squad Goals.

2045
01:16:43,434 --> 01:16:45,069
I don't have children of my own

2046
01:16:45,169 --> 01:16:47,605
so I did mention
that I wanted to try parenting.

2047
01:16:47,671 --> 01:16:50,708
And all of a sudden, that memory
kept playing in my mind nonstop.

2048
01:16:51,141 --> 01:16:52,376
Then I went, "Wait, that was it?"

2049
01:16:52,443 --> 01:16:54,044
That's what I was thinking earlier.

2050
01:16:54,445 --> 01:16:56,714
I can't believe you managed
to film me in that state.

2051
01:16:56,780 --> 01:16:58,782
So, well...

2052
01:16:58,849 --> 01:17:01,819
<i>One day,</i>
<i>I will have a child of my own.</i>

2053
01:17:02,119 --> 01:17:03,888
<i>Looking back</i>

2054
01:17:03,954 --> 01:17:06,190
<i>I've always been rather afraid</i>

2055
01:17:06,257 --> 01:17:08,292
<i>of little kids.</i>

2056
01:17:08,592 --> 01:17:09,960
<i>I had no idea what to do with them.</i>

2057
01:17:10,027 --> 01:17:11,996
<i>My mind was filled with questions.</i>

2058
01:17:12,062 --> 01:17:13,230
KEUN-SUK'S HOUSE SQUAD GOAL
BONDING WITH A BABY

2059
01:17:13,664 --> 01:17:15,666
I didn't think
they'd actually make it happen.

2060
01:17:15,733 --> 01:17:17,534
It was one of the random ideas
I just threw out there.

2061
01:17:18,202 --> 01:17:19,336
Are you good with babies?

2062
01:17:19,403 --> 01:17:20,905
There's nothing much to it.

2063
01:17:21,338 --> 01:17:23,774
- You're great with him.
- Not really.

2064
01:17:23,841 --> 01:17:25,342
We've got an angel here.

2065
01:17:25,409 --> 01:17:27,611
HE WOULD LIKE TO GET TO KNOW GYU-JIN
BUT CAN'T FIND THE COURAGE

2066
01:17:27,678 --> 01:17:29,113
Is it delicious?

2067
01:17:30,247 --> 01:17:33,050
The note says he should have dinner
between 6 p.m. and 7 p.m.

2068
01:17:33,117 --> 01:17:34,585
- What time is it?
- It's 7 p.m.

2069
01:17:34,652 --> 01:17:36,520
- Should I be feeding him this?
- "Unseasoned...

2070
01:17:36,987 --> 01:17:38,789
baby food." Gosh, he's ecstatic.

2071
01:17:38,856 --> 01:17:39,857
He wants more.

2072
01:17:43,227 --> 01:17:44,662
GYU-JIN EATS

2073
01:17:44,728 --> 01:17:47,598
A big bite for Gyu-jin.

2074
01:17:47,665 --> 01:17:48,666
AND EATS SOME MORE

2075
01:17:49,466 --> 01:17:51,035
IT'S YUMMY!

2076
01:17:51,268 --> 01:17:52,636
It's so good, right?

2077
01:17:53,170 --> 01:17:56,173
Make sure to chew everything, okay?

2078
01:17:56,240 --> 01:17:57,241
There you go.

2079
01:17:57,308 --> 01:17:59,009
It's almost gone, isn't it?

2080
01:17:59,410 --> 01:18:00,911
There's not so much left.

2081
01:18:02,613 --> 01:18:05,649
EVEN A SMALL MOVEMENT FROM GYU-JIN
MAKES KEUN-SUK JUMPY

2082
01:18:06,050 --> 01:18:07,584
He wants more. Give it to him.

2083
01:18:07,985 --> 01:18:10,521
Hang on, we have more
of his stuff by the entrance.

2084
01:18:10,587 --> 01:18:11,622
Really?

2085
01:18:11,689 --> 01:18:13,524
WITH THAT AS AN EXCUSE

2086
01:18:13,590 --> 01:18:17,461
KEUN-SUK FINDS TIME
TO PULL HIMSELF TOGETHER

2087
01:18:18,095 --> 01:18:21,498
COULD I BOND WITH THAT LITTLE BOY?

2088
01:18:21,565 --> 01:18:23,767
Did you swallow what you had?

2089
01:18:23,834 --> 01:18:25,436
Open wide for me.

2090
01:18:25,502 --> 01:18:27,404
You did finish everything.

2091
01:18:27,471 --> 01:18:29,139
FOODIE GYU-JIN
DOESN'T PLAY AROUND WITH FOOD

2092
01:18:31,408 --> 01:18:32,643
What on earth is this?

2093
01:18:33,210 --> 01:18:36,647
DISCOVERING THE WORLD OF BABY TOYS
FOR THE FIRST TIME IN 39 YEARS

2094
01:18:36,714 --> 01:18:37,848
But...

2095
01:18:38,682 --> 01:18:40,284
What could they do with this?

2096
01:18:44,221 --> 01:18:46,290
It doesn't make a sound or anything.

2097
01:18:47,124 --> 01:18:50,094
HE HAD FUN WITH TOY TRAINS
JUST YESTERDAY

2098
01:18:50,160 --> 01:18:51,495
They somehow have fun with this?

2099
01:18:51,562 --> 01:18:52,663
Is this fun for them?

2100
01:18:52,730 --> 01:18:53,998
WHAT ARE YOU DOING WITH MY TOYS?

2101
01:18:54,398 --> 01:18:55,599
I'm clueless.

2102
01:18:55,666 --> 01:18:56,767
Let's move them to the side.

2103
01:18:56,834 --> 01:18:57,835
Let's bring them further in

2104
01:18:57,901 --> 01:18:59,269
while Gyu-jin is distracted.

2105
01:19:00,571 --> 01:19:02,106
HUNGRY GYU-JIN
HANGS AROUND THE KITCHEN

2106
01:19:02,172 --> 01:19:03,173
- That should do it.
- Gyu-jin.

2107
01:19:03,240 --> 01:19:05,909
He hasn't had his dinner yet, right?

2108
01:19:06,844 --> 01:19:07,845
DID YOU SAY DINNER?

2109
01:19:07,911 --> 01:19:11,048
<i>"Gyu-jin only cries</i>
<i>when someone takes his food away."</i>

2110
01:19:11,915 --> 01:19:12,983
Gyu-jin.

2111
01:19:13,050 --> 01:19:15,219
- Do you want some food?
- What can he eat again?

2112
01:19:15,285 --> 01:19:16,286
Want some food?

2113
01:19:16,353 --> 01:19:18,022
- I'll get it ready soon.
- He's trying to escape.

2114
01:19:18,088 --> 01:19:19,089
- Hang on.
- Sorry, Gyu-jin.

2115
01:19:19,156 --> 01:19:20,157
- You can't.
- Pan-fried beef.

2116
01:19:20,224 --> 01:19:22,092
Gyu-jin.

2117
01:19:22,159 --> 01:19:24,028
I WANT MY FOOD NOW!

2118
01:19:24,094 --> 01:19:25,396
How are you this cute?

2119
01:19:25,796 --> 01:19:27,998
I'LL GET YOUR MEAL IN A FLASH!

2120
01:19:28,065 --> 01:19:30,534
URGENT MOVEMENTS

2121
01:19:31,101 --> 01:19:34,038
JAE-HYEON JOINS HER TO GET THE FOOD
READY BEFORE GYU-JIN STARTS CRYING

2122
01:19:34,371 --> 01:19:37,374
KEUN-SUK IS LEFT ALONE WITH GYU-JIN
DESPITE HIS FEAR OF LITTLE CHILDREN

2123
01:19:37,441 --> 01:19:39,476
PICKS UP HIS TOY

2124
01:19:39,843 --> 01:19:41,011
I'M BORED

2125
01:19:41,078 --> 01:19:42,379
What do you want to do with that cap?

2126
01:19:42,813 --> 01:19:43,814
Why do you want that cap?

2127
01:19:43,881 --> 01:19:45,149
OBSERVING FROM AFAR

2128
01:19:45,516 --> 01:19:48,152
HE'S TOO SCARED TO APPROACH HIM,
BUT HIS GAZE NEVER LEAVES HIM

2129
01:19:48,752 --> 01:19:52,056
LET'S PLAY TOGETHER, UNCLE KEUN-SUK

2130
01:19:52,589 --> 01:19:56,026
ALL HE CAN DO IS OBSERVE GYU-JIN
WHILE SITTING DOWN

2131
01:19:56,093 --> 01:20:00,798
AND STANDING UP

2132
01:20:01,165 --> 01:20:04,134
JUST HOW DO I GIVE HIM A GOOD TIME?

2133
01:20:08,372 --> 01:20:10,340
What is this, Gyu-jin?

2134
01:20:12,176 --> 01:20:13,177
Why do you want it?

2135
01:20:13,243 --> 01:20:14,745
STILL HAS NO CLUE WHAT TO DO

2136
01:20:17,648 --> 01:20:19,750
Should we play with this?
What button should we press?

2137
01:20:22,019 --> 01:20:23,187
STUDIES HIS FACE

2138
01:20:23,253 --> 01:20:24,388
Do you want me to open this?

2139
01:20:25,956 --> 01:20:27,357
There we go.

2140
01:20:27,424 --> 01:20:28,425
HOORAY

2141
01:20:28,492 --> 01:20:31,495
MINI PARENTING SESSION LED BY GYU-JIN

2142
01:20:31,562 --> 01:20:33,897
So we have to place
little pieces there?

2143
01:20:33,964 --> 01:20:35,966
Gosh, I had no idea.

2144
01:20:36,733 --> 01:20:38,902
It's the other way around.
Hold it like this.

2145
01:20:39,336 --> 01:20:41,171
Slide it right in. Go on.

2146
01:20:43,307 --> 01:20:44,808
Good job.

2147
01:20:45,809 --> 01:20:47,177
Everything's in its right place.

2148
01:20:47,244 --> 01:20:49,179
Happy birthday.

2149
01:20:49,913 --> 01:20:51,882
CHECKS KEUN-SUK'S REACTION

2150
01:20:53,584 --> 01:20:56,286
All done. Great job.

2151
01:20:57,921 --> 01:20:58,922
Shall we press this?

2152
01:20:58,989 --> 01:21:00,157
LITTLE DID THIS WANNABE-DAD KNOW

2153
01:21:00,224 --> 01:21:03,260
THAT YOU HAVE TO PLAY
THE SAME GAME HUNDREDS OF TIMES

2154
01:21:03,327 --> 01:21:04,695
How exciting, right?

2155
01:21:04,928 --> 01:21:06,230
You're so hyped up.

2156
01:21:07,664 --> 01:21:09,333
GET YOUR ENERGY UP!

2157
01:21:11,168 --> 01:21:14,404
IS THIS ENOUGH?

2158
01:21:14,471 --> 01:21:17,207
THE BEST THIS 39-YEAR-OLD CAN MUSTER

2159
01:21:18,108 --> 01:21:19,710
Good job.

2160
01:21:19,776 --> 01:21:20,811
SATISFIED

2161
01:21:21,245 --> 01:21:22,379
MEANWHILE

2162
01:21:22,446 --> 01:21:25,582
SOO-JIN IS PREPARING GYU-JIN'S DINNER
FOLLOWING HIS MOTHER'S RECIPE

2163
01:21:25,649 --> 01:21:26,984
SHE'S WORKING QUICKLY

2164
01:21:27,050 --> 01:21:28,886
<i>- Shall I set his meal table?</i>
<i>- Aren't you hungry?</i>

2165
01:21:28,952 --> 01:21:30,721
<i>- Where should we feed him? Here?</i>
<i>- Right here.</i>

2166
01:21:30,787 --> 01:21:31,855
Okay, then.

2167
01:21:31,922 --> 01:21:33,090
UNCLE JAE-HYEON SETS THE TABLE

2168
01:21:33,157 --> 01:21:35,392
AS IF ON CUE,
GYU-JIN JUMPS TO HIS FEET

2169
01:21:35,692 --> 01:21:37,628
STRIDES UP TO THE TABLE

2170
01:21:37,694 --> 01:21:40,297
Hey, look. He's sitting at the table.

2171
01:21:41,131 --> 01:21:42,833
Here's your dinner, Gyu-jin.

2172
01:21:43,467 --> 01:21:45,135
- Your food is here.
- Your food is here.

2173
01:21:46,336 --> 01:21:48,539
- Your food is here.
- Let's eat together.

2174
01:21:49,139 --> 01:21:51,208
- Your food is here.
- How exciting, right?

2175
01:21:51,275 --> 01:21:53,577
- Wait, it's still hot.
- Did I make too much?

2176
01:21:53,644 --> 01:21:56,747
HOPEFULLY, HE WILL EAT WELL

2177
01:21:57,047 --> 01:21:58,782
CHECKS THE TEMPERATURE FIRST

2178
01:21:59,216 --> 01:22:00,317
He's good.

2179
01:22:00,617 --> 01:22:01,919
He's good.

2180
01:22:01,985 --> 01:22:03,487
JEALOUS

2181
01:22:03,820 --> 01:22:05,088
The rice might be hot.

2182
01:22:05,155 --> 01:22:06,790
A BIG BITE

2183
01:22:07,291 --> 01:22:08,292
It's delicious.

2184
01:22:08,358 --> 01:22:09,593
What do you think?

2185
01:22:09,893 --> 01:22:11,929
- It's so good.
- Yum, yum.

2186
01:22:12,629 --> 01:22:13,797
Want to try this?

2187
01:22:14,565 --> 01:22:16,066
Want to try this?

2188
01:22:18,235 --> 01:22:19,403
You're eating like a champ.

2189
01:22:19,469 --> 01:22:20,704
AMAZED TO SEE HIM EAT

2190
01:22:21,471 --> 01:22:22,673
Let's get your bib on.

2191
01:22:23,373 --> 01:22:25,542
STRETCHES HIS NECK FOR THE BIB

2192
01:22:26,176 --> 01:22:27,844
- What's with this kid?
- Did you see that?

2193
01:22:27,911 --> 01:22:28,912
Let's get your bib on.

2194
01:22:29,379 --> 01:22:32,349
15-MONTH-OLD GYU-JIN
IS A WELL-BEHAVED GENIUS

2195
01:22:32,416 --> 01:22:34,218
- What's with this kid?
- Did you see that?

2196
01:22:34,284 --> 01:22:35,285
He did this.

2197
01:22:35,352 --> 01:22:36,553
Seriously, what on earth?

2198
01:22:37,754 --> 01:22:38,755
THAT WAS NOTHING

2199
01:22:38,822 --> 01:22:41,291
- He's so gentle, isn't he?
- I mean...

2200
01:22:41,358 --> 01:22:43,560
He's got everything sorted out.

2201
01:22:43,627 --> 01:22:46,163
To think he's only 15 months old.

2202
01:22:46,230 --> 01:22:47,297
What do you want to eat next?

2203
01:22:47,364 --> 01:22:49,199
- Do you want the beef?
- Hurry and serve him.

2204
01:22:49,833 --> 01:22:51,735
- There we go.
- Hurry.

2205
01:22:51,802 --> 01:22:53,570
- Here's your food.
- Open wide.

2206
01:22:53,637 --> 01:22:54,972
COMMUNICATES HIS NEEDS EASILY

2207
01:22:58,375 --> 01:23:01,411
GAZES AT HIM FIXEDLY

2208
01:23:01,478 --> 01:23:03,513
What kind of creature is he?

2209
01:23:04,848 --> 01:23:07,017
THE MORE KEUN-SUK LOOKS AT GYU-JIN,
THE MORE AMAZED HE IS

2210
01:23:07,217 --> 01:23:08,285
Oh, sure.

2211
01:23:08,352 --> 01:23:10,988
A child like Gyu-jin is...

2212
01:23:11,054 --> 01:23:12,956
- Would you be up for raising them?
- Of course.

2213
01:23:13,023 --> 01:23:14,324
Is he on the gentle side?

2214
01:23:14,391 --> 01:23:16,159
He's the gentlest soul.

2215
01:23:16,226 --> 01:23:17,527
To be fair, he hasn't cried once yet.

2216
01:23:17,594 --> 01:23:19,363
No, he didn't.

2217
01:23:19,429 --> 01:23:21,565
On top of that,
he's surrounded by three strangers.

2218
01:23:21,632 --> 01:23:22,833
GENTLE AND WELL-MANNERED GYU-JIN

2219
01:23:22,899 --> 01:23:25,502
Little children like him terrify me.

2220
01:23:25,569 --> 01:23:28,805
Even after washing myself,
I'm still afraid they'll get tainted

2221
01:23:29,072 --> 01:23:31,375
- when I approach them.
- I feel you.

2222
01:23:32,009 --> 01:23:34,011
So I just can't get close to them.

2223
01:23:34,077 --> 01:23:35,279
HE'S BEEN REFRAINING CONTACT

2224
01:23:35,345 --> 01:23:36,480
I'm amazed by them, though.

2225
01:23:37,281 --> 01:23:40,450
I guess you didn't have many chances
to see little children up close.

2226
01:23:40,517 --> 01:23:42,185
NOT REALLY, NO

2227
01:23:42,252 --> 01:23:43,687
I'm really clueless here.

2228
01:23:43,754 --> 01:23:45,422
WITH 34 YEARS OF WORK EXPERIENCE,
A 15-MONTH-OLD STILL SCARES HIM

2229
01:23:45,489 --> 01:23:47,157
I've never tried babysitting

2230
01:23:47,224 --> 01:23:49,393
so I just mentioned it
as a possible House Squad Goal.

2231
01:23:49,459 --> 01:23:51,128
BEING A FATHER IS
ON HIS ULTIMATE BUCKET LIST

2232
01:23:51,194 --> 01:23:53,063
I somehow got to try this today.

2233
01:23:53,130 --> 01:23:54,464
WILL HE BE ABLE TO DO WELL?

2234
01:23:54,531 --> 01:23:56,333
Do you want to hold Gyu-jin?

2235
01:23:56,400 --> 01:23:57,868
So soft and squishy.

2236
01:23:57,934 --> 01:23:59,102
- Come closer.
- Won't he cry?

2237
01:23:59,169 --> 01:24:00,404
No way. Come closer.

2238
01:24:01,672 --> 01:24:03,106
Support his back, okay?

2239
01:24:03,573 --> 01:24:04,608
Gyu-jin.

2240
01:24:05,509 --> 01:24:06,677
Come here.

2241
01:24:07,177 --> 01:24:08,879
He's gotten heavier.

2242
01:24:10,113 --> 01:24:13,283
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

2243
01:24:13,717 --> 01:24:14,851
He weighs about 8kg to 10kg.

2244
01:24:14,918 --> 01:24:16,486
- He feels like a balloon.
- Right?

2245
01:24:16,553 --> 01:24:18,088
He just leans on you completely.

2246
01:24:18,155 --> 01:24:19,356
UNFAMILIAR WARMTH

2247
01:24:19,423 --> 01:24:21,958
- Hey, he's holding Jae-hyeon's hand.
- Maybe he weighs about 10kg.

2248
01:24:22,426 --> 01:24:24,361
- Keun-suk.
- Not that much, though.

2249
01:24:24,428 --> 01:24:26,196
Somewhere between 8kg and 10kg, then.

2250
01:24:27,364 --> 01:24:29,499
- His cheeks are just...
- Just like Shin-chan's, right?

2251
01:24:29,566 --> 01:24:31,034
- Incredible.
- It's so cute.

2252
01:24:31,101 --> 01:24:32,269
FIRST TIME HOLDING A BABY

2253
01:24:32,336 --> 01:24:34,237
AFTER YEARS OF WATCHING
FROM THE SIDELINES

2254
01:24:35,072 --> 01:24:36,573
- Yes.
- Sure.

2255
01:24:36,640 --> 01:24:38,642
AFTER LISTENING ATTENTIVELY

2256
01:24:38,709 --> 01:24:40,210
TO EVERY SOUND GYU-JIN MAKES

2257
01:24:40,277 --> 01:24:41,311
So adorable.

2258
01:24:42,145 --> 01:24:43,814
CHUCKLES

2259
01:24:43,880 --> 01:24:45,082
Am I doing this right, though?

2260
01:24:46,516 --> 01:24:48,652
Just holding him is...

2261
01:24:49,653 --> 01:24:51,221
HE'S LOVING IT, ALL RIGHT

2262
01:24:51,288 --> 01:24:52,789
- How's this?
- Want some egg?

2263
01:24:52,856 --> 01:24:54,124
Do you want more rice or more eggs?

2264
01:24:54,191 --> 01:24:55,525
- What's up?
- Where do you want to go?

2265
01:24:55,592 --> 01:24:57,361
- Want to play?
- He's pushing me away.

2266
01:24:57,427 --> 01:24:59,796
- Hey, he wants to get up.
- I got you.

2267
01:24:59,863 --> 01:25:01,865
- We can finish the leftovers.
- Of course.

2268
01:25:03,834 --> 01:25:05,469
- Just like real parents.
- You bet.

2269
01:25:05,535 --> 01:25:07,170
- We eat his leftover food.
- Yes, we do.

2270
01:25:07,237 --> 01:25:08,505
That's right.

2271
01:25:09,272 --> 01:25:12,943
HE LOOKS PLENTY SATISFIED
FROM THE BACK

2272
01:25:13,543 --> 01:25:15,645
- Are we sure he's done, though?
- Let's observe for now.

2273
01:25:17,280 --> 01:25:18,448
Let's eat the rest.

2274
01:25:18,515 --> 01:25:22,652
HANDS-ON PARENTING PRACTICE
FOR THE FUTURE

2275
01:25:23,220 --> 01:25:24,354
It's Korean beef.

2276
01:25:25,555 --> 01:25:27,724
SMILES SHYLY

2277
01:25:30,994 --> 01:25:32,863
When he locks eyes and smiles

2278
01:25:32,929 --> 01:25:35,132
- your brain turns to mush.
- Right?

2279
01:25:38,769 --> 01:25:43,006
KEUN-SUK CAN'T SEEM
TO LOOK AWAY FROM GYU-JIN

2280
01:25:43,073 --> 01:25:44,074
So cute.

2281
01:25:46,176 --> 01:25:47,744
WOULD-BE FATHER
IS GRINNING EAR TO EAR

2282
01:25:47,811 --> 01:25:49,413
Hey, he's actually dancing.

2283
01:25:49,946 --> 01:25:51,548
It's time for your cold medicine.

2284
01:25:51,615 --> 01:25:53,183
FEELING CONFIDENT,
HE WANTS TO GIVE HIM MEDICINE

2285
01:25:53,250 --> 01:25:54,885
Come to me.

2286
01:25:55,452 --> 01:25:56,686
Come to me.

2287
01:25:56,753 --> 01:25:58,989
TRAILS AFTER HIM

2288
01:25:59,055 --> 01:26:00,891
Come here. You've got to have some.

2289
01:26:00,957 --> 01:26:03,059
It's cold outside. Come on.

2290
01:26:03,560 --> 01:26:04,761
Come here.

2291
01:26:05,962 --> 01:26:07,230
Here's your medicine. Open wide.

2292
01:26:07,297 --> 01:26:11,201
KEUN-SUK USED
TO BE AFRAID OF CHILDREN

2293
01:26:11,268 --> 01:26:15,338
BUT HE CAN NOW HOLD TODDLERS
LIKE NOBODY'S BUSINESS

2294
01:26:15,405 --> 01:26:16,840
TAKES IN THE SYRUP

2295
01:26:17,741 --> 01:26:19,276
- He's good with medicine, too?
- Yes.

2296
01:26:19,342 --> 01:26:22,145
LITTLE FOODIE CAN EAT
AND DRINK ANYTHING

2297
01:26:22,846 --> 01:26:24,614
- Hey, he did it.
- Did he finish the bottle?

2298
01:26:24,681 --> 01:26:26,450
And I managed to feed him his syrup.

2299
01:26:26,516 --> 01:26:27,984
I actually did it.

2300
01:26:28,051 --> 01:26:29,119
Do you want some more?

2301
01:26:29,186 --> 01:26:31,221
Keun-suk gave Gyu-jin his cold syrup.

2302
01:26:31,288 --> 01:26:33,190
BOTH OF YOU ARE SO CUTE

2303
01:26:33,256 --> 01:26:34,624
<i>All done now.</i>

2304
01:26:34,958 --> 01:26:36,726
<i>- You finished it. Good job.</i>
<i>- So cute.</i>

2305
01:26:37,494 --> 01:26:38,962
Send me that photo.

2306
01:26:39,029 --> 01:26:41,131
- I'll send it to our group chat.
- I want it.

2307
01:26:41,198 --> 01:26:42,332
Let's eat.

2308
01:26:42,399 --> 01:26:43,500
What's wrong?

2309
01:26:43,567 --> 01:26:44,801
THESE TWO HAVE A QUICK MEAL

2310
01:26:44,868 --> 01:26:45,969
What's up?

2311
01:26:47,838 --> 01:26:49,172
Strawberry!

2312
01:26:49,239 --> 01:26:50,874
STARES INTO THE VOID

2313
01:26:51,708 --> 01:26:53,510
It feels terrible

2314
01:26:53,577 --> 01:26:55,145
to make Keun-suk watch him alone.

2315
01:26:55,212 --> 01:26:57,481
- Don't feel that way.
- Would his parents feel this way?

2316
01:26:57,547 --> 01:27:00,083
- We're taking turns anyway.
- Yeah, we're taking turns.

2317
01:27:01,551 --> 01:27:03,553
And as a trade-off,
we can't take our time with food.

2318
01:27:03,620 --> 01:27:05,655
YOU'RE LUCKY TO EAT AT ALL
WHEN YOU HAVE A LITTLE CHILD

2319
01:27:06,423 --> 01:27:09,392
GYU-JIN'S LEFTOVERS

2320
01:27:09,459 --> 01:27:11,862
Want to play with this, Gyu-jin?

2321
01:27:11,928 --> 01:27:13,029
IN A RUSH

2322
01:27:13,096 --> 01:27:15,098
SHE'S WOLFING IT DOWN
TO RELIEVE KEUN-SUK QUICKLY

2323
01:27:15,165 --> 01:27:16,633
- I'll be done in a minute.
- I'll switch with him.

2324
01:27:16,700 --> 01:27:18,168
HE'S DOING THE SAME

2325
01:27:18,235 --> 01:27:19,903
Gosh, you're a biter.

2326
01:27:20,403 --> 01:27:22,239
If you hold on to it,
I can't brush your teeth.

2327
01:27:22,839 --> 01:27:24,508
Open wide.

2328
01:27:25,709 --> 01:27:29,613
JUST SCARF DOWN EVERYTHING

2329
01:27:29,679 --> 01:27:31,281
NOW KEUN-SUK GETS HIS TURN TO EAT

2330
01:27:31,348 --> 01:27:33,149
Come here, Gyu-jin.

2331
01:27:34,351 --> 01:27:37,320
UNCLE JAE-HYEON IS NOW IN CHARGE
OF LOOKING AFTER GYU-JIN

2332
01:27:37,888 --> 01:27:38,889
Roar.

2333
01:27:38,955 --> 01:27:39,956
GIGGLES

2334
01:27:40,290 --> 01:27:41,925
- Roar.
- Gosh, look at him.

2335
01:27:42,325 --> 01:27:43,326
GIGGLES

2336
01:27:44,027 --> 01:27:45,762
He's downright giggling.

2337
01:27:45,829 --> 01:27:47,497
He's laughing so hard.

2338
01:27:48,064 --> 01:27:50,767
SOMEHOW FEELS BETRAYED

2339
01:27:50,834 --> 01:27:51,902
It's exciting, isn't it?

2340
01:27:51,968 --> 01:27:57,374
PARENTING REQUIRES GREAT STAMINA

2341
01:27:59,442 --> 01:28:00,443
Bet you're psyched.

2342
01:28:00,510 --> 01:28:01,511
GIGGLING SOUND WON'T STOP

2343
01:28:01,578 --> 01:28:02,646
I got you.

2344
01:28:04,314 --> 01:28:05,949
Gosh, you're scared.

2345
01:28:06,016 --> 01:28:07,551
HE DIDN'T SMILE AT ALL
WHEN HE WAS WITH ME

2346
01:28:08,351 --> 01:28:09,986
LAUGHING NONSTOP

2347
01:28:10,053 --> 01:28:11,388
Gosh, you're scared.

2348
01:28:11,454 --> 01:28:13,189
GYU-JIN AND JAE-HYEON
ARE MAKING KEUN-SUK JEALOUS

2349
01:28:13,623 --> 01:28:16,259
SAD

2350
01:28:16,660 --> 01:28:17,827
SOO-JIN JOINS THEM

2351
01:28:17,894 --> 01:28:18,929
You little punk.

2352
01:28:19,229 --> 01:28:21,431
If you ask me

2353
01:28:21,498 --> 01:28:23,967
you guys are using up
all your energy in this short time.

2354
01:28:24,034 --> 01:28:26,369
You need to adopt
a low-stimulation style like mine.

2355
01:28:28,004 --> 01:28:29,706
BUT I WANT
HIGH-STIMULATION PARENTING!

2356
01:28:29,773 --> 01:28:31,308
I'm going to get you, Gyu-jin.

2357
01:28:32,008 --> 01:28:33,076
Here he comes.

2358
01:28:33,143 --> 01:28:34,277
There you are.

2359
01:28:35,078 --> 01:28:36,813
LOST IN THE GAME

2360
01:28:36,880 --> 01:28:39,449
No, you can't go. I got you now.

2361
01:28:39,516 --> 01:28:40,817
WITH NO CARE FOR JEALOUS KEUN-SUK

2362
01:28:43,119 --> 01:28:44,854
PANTS

2363
01:28:46,122 --> 01:28:47,724
I'm going to get you.

2364
01:28:47,791 --> 01:28:49,359
SWEATING BUCKETS

2365
01:28:49,426 --> 01:28:50,427
You're the best, Gyu-jin.

2366
01:28:51,494 --> 01:28:52,495
I got you.

2367
01:28:52,562 --> 01:28:54,297
THEY SACRIFICE THEIR ENERGY
FOR GYU-JIN'S HAPPINESS

2368
01:28:54,364 --> 01:28:55,365
Oh, dear.

2369
01:28:55,432 --> 01:28:59,235
IN THE END,
THE 87ERS ARE ALL EXHAUSTED

2370
01:29:00,337 --> 01:29:02,839
We've all worked together
to take care of one little kid.

2371
01:29:03,473 --> 01:29:05,041
I'm proud that we did our best.

2372
01:29:06,176 --> 01:29:09,245
GYU-JIN IS TIRED, TOO

2373
01:29:10,180 --> 01:29:13,283
HE HAS CHOSEN JAE-HYEON TO HOLD HIM

2374
01:29:17,487 --> 01:29:19,589
Do you think I could be a parent?

2375
01:29:20,523 --> 01:29:22,559
<i>- Could I do it?</i>
- Of course.

2376
01:29:22,626 --> 01:29:24,961
FROM MARRIAGE TO PARENTING,
KEUN-SUK HAS MUCH TO CONSIDER

2377
01:29:25,028 --> 01:29:27,697
AS HIS 40TH BIRTHDAY APPROACHES

2378
01:29:28,131 --> 01:29:31,234
<i>- How would I have treated him</i>
- Want to go to Uncle Keun-suk?

2379
01:29:31,301 --> 01:29:33,603
- Want to go to him?
<i>- if he had been my son?</i>

2380
01:29:33,670 --> 01:29:35,772
<i>I thought about that a lot, too.</i>

2381
01:29:38,041 --> 01:29:42,412
I would have to put my children
above all else, including myself.

2382
01:29:42,679 --> 01:29:46,049
When such a precious being
enters my life

2383
01:29:46,516 --> 01:29:50,286
I will have to reach
a new level of maturity

2384
01:29:50,520 --> 01:29:52,555
let myself go

2385
01:29:52,622 --> 01:29:55,792
and channel the love
I've always directed at myself

2386
01:29:55,859 --> 01:29:57,260
to my child.

2387
01:29:58,662 --> 01:29:59,929
WHILE HE WANTS TO BE A FATHER ONE DAY

2388
01:29:59,996 --> 01:30:01,164
Am I doing this right, though?

2389
01:30:02,732 --> 01:30:04,801
Just holding him is...

2390
01:30:04,868 --> 01:30:08,738
HE KNOWS A PRECIOUS NEW LIFE
COMES WITH BURDENS AND QUESTIONS

2391
01:30:08,805 --> 01:30:10,974
Maybe I'll get there
once I become a father.

2392
01:30:11,307 --> 01:30:12,842
But for now

2393
01:30:13,743 --> 01:30:14,844
it feels like a huge challenge.

2394
01:30:19,449 --> 01:30:20,450
BYE-BYE, AUNT AND UNCLES

2395
01:30:20,517 --> 01:30:21,651
- Thank you.
- No problem.

2396
01:30:21,718 --> 01:30:23,353
- Drive safely.
- Thank you.

2397
01:30:23,653 --> 01:30:25,689
- Take care. Bye-bye.
- Let's help her with her bags.

2398
01:30:25,755 --> 01:30:27,057
Sure, I can carry them.

2399
01:30:27,123 --> 01:30:28,158
Bye.

2400
01:30:28,224 --> 01:30:30,160
THEY ARE STILL FIGURING IT OUT

2401
01:30:30,226 --> 01:30:31,461
My gosh, he's so cute.

2402
01:30:31,528 --> 01:30:34,464
BUT THE EXPERIENCE HAS HELPED THEM
LOOK FORWARD TO THE FUTURE

2403
01:30:35,031 --> 01:30:36,232
Let's keep the door open.

2404
01:30:36,299 --> 01:30:37,901
- It's too hot inside.
- Okay.

2405
01:30:39,169 --> 01:30:40,270
Gosh.

2406
01:30:40,336 --> 01:30:42,105
Turns out we're pretty energetic.

2407
01:30:42,472 --> 01:30:43,640
We've still got it.

2408
01:30:43,707 --> 01:30:46,176
- I know we had dinner...
- It was really...

2409
01:30:46,242 --> 01:30:47,644
- Hungry, right?
- Totally.

2410
01:30:47,711 --> 01:30:48,778
HUNGRY AGAIN

2411
01:30:50,046 --> 01:30:52,148
Did you check Daniel's message?

2412
01:30:52,215 --> 01:30:53,450
- "Pigeon, right?"
- "Pigeon, right?"

2413
01:30:55,285 --> 01:30:57,454
He must think it was AI-generated.

2414
01:30:57,787 --> 01:30:58,955
Unbelievable.

2415
01:30:59,622 --> 01:31:00,824
He's so funny.

2416
01:31:04,294 --> 01:31:07,697
A baby completely changes
the atmosphere.

2417
01:31:08,598 --> 01:31:11,000
SOMEHOW, IT FEELS EMPTY

2418
01:31:11,067 --> 01:31:12,936
Did they all go to bed?
It's too soon for that.

2419
01:31:13,002 --> 01:31:14,537
Hey, someone's home.

2420
01:31:15,739 --> 01:31:16,873
Hey, you guys.

2421
01:31:16,940 --> 01:31:18,074
What on earth?

2422
01:31:18,975 --> 01:31:20,176
What happened?

2423
01:31:20,744 --> 01:31:21,845
My gosh.

2424
01:31:21,911 --> 01:31:23,012
STARTLED

2425
01:31:23,079 --> 01:31:24,080
What's all this?

2426
01:31:24,447 --> 01:31:25,615
- Welcome.
- Why do we have these?

2427
01:31:25,682 --> 01:31:27,283
- Welcome home.
- Was it real?

2428
01:31:28,151 --> 01:31:29,886
IT'S TIME FOR A LITTLE PRANK

2429
01:31:29,953 --> 01:31:32,322
- What are these for?
- He's sleeping.

2430
01:31:32,388 --> 01:31:33,423
QUIET

2431
01:31:33,790 --> 01:31:35,158
WE HAVE A SLEEPING BABY HERE?

2432
01:31:35,225 --> 01:31:36,926
- It must be real.
- In the room?

2433
01:31:37,160 --> 01:31:38,428
He's in there.

2434
01:31:38,495 --> 01:31:40,096
PERFECT PARTNERS IN MISCHIEF MAKING

2435
01:31:40,597 --> 01:31:42,198
STILL UNSURE

2436
01:31:42,265 --> 01:31:43,333
Is this for real?

2437
01:31:43,600 --> 01:31:46,469
Go to my room and see for yourselves.

2438
01:31:46,736 --> 01:31:48,805
He's sleeping in my bed.
He's a perfect angel.

2439
01:31:48,872 --> 01:31:50,373
This wasn't a prank like the pigeon?

2440
01:31:50,440 --> 01:31:51,441
It's real, okay?

2441
01:31:51,508 --> 01:31:54,110
AS IF BEWITCHED

2442
01:31:54,177 --> 01:31:56,746
SHE HEADS TO SOO-JIN'S ROOM

2443
01:31:56,813 --> 01:31:58,314
He's asleep.

2444
01:31:58,581 --> 01:31:59,749
Hush.

2445
01:31:59,816 --> 01:32:00,817
CAREFUL

2446
01:32:01,885 --> 01:32:03,086
Where's the kid?

2447
01:32:03,353 --> 01:32:04,788
Right there, Do-yeon.

2448
01:32:06,523 --> 01:32:07,524
Behind the duvet.

2449
01:32:07,590 --> 01:32:09,225
Why can't I see him?

2450
01:32:09,859 --> 01:32:12,428
- Where is he?
- I can't seem to find him.

2451
01:32:12,495 --> 01:32:13,696
ONLY KIND PEOPLE CAN SEE HIM

2452
01:32:13,763 --> 01:32:15,064
Hush.

2453
01:32:15,732 --> 01:32:17,100
- But that's her sweater.
- Hush.

2454
01:32:17,400 --> 01:32:18,535
SHAKING LIKE A LEAF

2455
01:32:18,601 --> 01:32:20,203
TWITCHES

2456
01:32:20,270 --> 01:32:21,304
FLINGS THE DUVET OFF

2457
01:32:21,371 --> 01:32:23,006
- What the...
- So it was a lie?

2458
01:32:23,072 --> 01:32:24,307
- Did you play us?
- You lied to us?

2459
01:32:24,374 --> 01:32:25,742
Come on, guys.

2460
01:32:25,809 --> 01:32:27,944
It's pigeon business all over again.

2461
01:32:28,144 --> 01:32:29,145
He was here, but he left.

2462
01:32:29,212 --> 01:32:30,580
- I don't buy it.
- He left?

2463
01:32:30,647 --> 01:32:32,382
Why else would we have
these fences, then?

2464
01:32:32,448 --> 01:32:33,716
Why did you do it?

2465
01:32:33,783 --> 01:32:36,085
Did you guys go this far
to pull off a prank?

2466
01:32:36,152 --> 01:32:38,621
Was it your passion project?

2467
01:32:38,688 --> 01:32:41,191
- He has it in him to pull it off.
- That's true.

2468
01:32:41,257 --> 01:32:42,859
You're blaming me again?

2469
01:32:42,926 --> 01:32:44,494
- Seriously.
- I'm not blaming you.

2470
01:32:44,561 --> 01:32:46,062
I can't believe this.

2471
01:32:46,129 --> 01:32:47,931
Did you really go to Chuncheon?

2472
01:32:47,997 --> 01:32:49,199
Of course.

2473
01:32:49,666 --> 01:32:50,867
I bet that photo was a fake.

2474
01:32:50,934 --> 01:32:52,402
A hoax like the pigeon incident.

2475
01:32:52,468 --> 01:32:54,204
Are we going to keep
suspecting one another?

2476
01:32:54,270 --> 01:32:56,606
- Even if we had tried...
- I bet that's another AI scam.

2477
01:32:56,673 --> 01:32:59,542
You think the AI could give you
an old-school photo print like this?

2478
01:32:59,609 --> 01:33:02,045
THERE IS NO TRUST
BETWEEN THE HOUSEMATES

2479
01:33:02,111 --> 01:33:04,414
- You think an AI could do this?
- It can merge your faces into this.

2480
01:33:04,480 --> 01:33:06,249
It's the real thing.

2481
01:33:06,583 --> 01:33:09,619
- Good job today.
- Good job today.

2482
01:33:11,321 --> 01:33:13,823
IT'S BEST TO WIND DOWN WITH THE FAM

2483
01:33:13,890 --> 01:33:15,491
The parenting exercise drained me.

2484
01:33:15,558 --> 01:33:16,559
It's so refreshing.

2485
01:33:16,893 --> 01:33:19,362
After we wrap this up

2486
01:33:19,429 --> 01:33:20,730
what are we doing tomorrow?

2487
01:33:20,797 --> 01:33:22,065
Tomorrow?

2488
01:33:22,131 --> 01:33:23,333
EVERYONE WILL BE HOME FOR A CHANGE

2489
01:33:23,399 --> 01:33:24,534
DEEP IN THOUGHT

2490
01:33:24,601 --> 01:33:27,036
Why don't we each invite

2491
01:33:27,103 --> 01:33:29,239
a best friend home?

2492
01:33:29,906 --> 01:33:31,107
Can you think of anyone to invite?

2493
01:33:31,808 --> 01:33:32,842
Who should I invite?

2494
01:33:32,909 --> 01:33:35,511
There's someone who comes to mind.

2495
01:33:36,045 --> 01:33:37,881
- Who is it?
- Well...

2496
01:33:38,248 --> 01:33:39,582
He's practically my mini-me.

2497
01:33:39,649 --> 01:33:40,783
- You?
- Your mini-me?

2498
01:33:42,619 --> 01:33:43,853
My friend loves Keun-suk.

2499
01:33:43,920 --> 01:33:45,154
SOMEONE'S IN LOVE WITH KEUN-SUK?

2500
01:33:45,221 --> 01:33:48,491
You're just messing with me again
with false hope.

2501
01:33:48,558 --> 01:33:49,859
My friend's a superstar.

2502
01:33:51,194 --> 01:33:52,262
What's more

2503
01:33:52,528 --> 01:33:53,563
he's handsome.

2504
01:33:54,597 --> 01:33:55,632
- Is he an actor?
- Yeah.

2505
01:33:55,698 --> 01:33:56,699
SUDDENLY INTERESTED

2506
01:33:56,766 --> 01:33:58,201
- He's an absolute A-lister.
- Really?

2507
01:33:58,268 --> 01:33:59,402
ANTICIPATION FOR THE GUESTS GROWS

2508
01:33:59,869 --> 01:34:04,107
WHO WILL MAKE THE GUEST LIST
OF THE GUGI-DONG YARD PARTY?

2509
01:34:04,474 --> 01:34:05,875
Why don't we hold a sports day?

2510
01:34:06,442 --> 01:34:08,077
A SPORTS DAY?

2511
01:34:08,144 --> 01:34:09,746
- Let's do it.
- Sounds good to me.

2512
01:34:10,079 --> 01:34:11,981
Sure, sounds like fun.

2513
01:34:12,048 --> 01:34:15,385
KEEP CALM AND CRUSH THEM ALL

2514
01:34:16,085 --> 01:34:18,488
TRUE MADNESS

2515
01:34:18,554 --> 01:34:20,323
CHILLS

2516
01:34:20,390 --> 01:34:22,025
THE COMPETITIVE GODDESS IS DOWN

2517
01:34:22,358 --> 01:34:26,062
SPORTS DAY IS TURNING INTO CHAOS

2518
01:34:26,129 --> 01:34:27,630
SNEAKY

2519
01:34:27,997 --> 01:34:29,465
Stop moving, all of you!

2520
01:34:29,532 --> 01:34:30,566
You sh******s.

2521
01:34:30,633 --> 01:34:31,801
NO DIGNITY NOR MANNERS

2522
01:34:31,868 --> 01:34:34,771
CHAOTIC SPORTS DAY FOR THE FORTIES
COMING SOON

2523
01:34:35,471 --> 01:34:36,940
<i>I think I'm overthinking things.</i>

2524
01:34:37,006 --> 01:34:39,642
AN UNEXPECTED CONFESSION
BY THE CHEERFUL DO-YEON

2525
01:34:39,709 --> 01:34:42,578
<i>Do-yeon had already been worn out.</i>

2526
01:34:42,645 --> 01:34:43,646
TEARS OF EXHAUSTION

2527
01:34:43,713 --> 01:34:45,915
<i>Let's get it out of our system</i>
<i>before we leave.</i>

2528
01:34:45,982 --> 01:34:48,518
WHAT HAPPENED TO DO-YEON?

2529
01:34:53,222 --> 01:34:55,224
Subtitles by Jeongwoo Kim
